1
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:09,801
We're getting closer to the end, everyone.

2
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,429
Let's go!

3
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:14,222
Let's go!

4
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:21,104
I really did want to sing
at least once before we all left.

5
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:23,565
I thought it would be
a beautiful moment for us to have.

6
00:00:23,648 --> 00:00:26,443
So I sang right from the heart
for the people who came all the way here.

7
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:31,114
"SUDDEN SHOWER" BY ECLIPSE

8
00:00:31,197 --> 00:00:35,535
<i>I hoped it wouldn't stop </i>

9
00:00:35,618 --> 00:00:36,870
Wow, this is unreal.

10
00:00:36,953 --> 00:00:42,292
<i>On the day you first came to me </i>

11
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:43,501
MESMERIZED

12
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:44,711
I'm gonna cry.

13
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:51,718
<i>I prayed it wouldn't be Just passing rain</i>

14
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:56,473
<i>I longed so desperately for it to last </i>

15
00:00:57,849 --> 00:00:59,768
- That's really nice.
- It's great.

16
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:03,021
<i>Do you know how I feel too? </i>

17
00:01:03,104 --> 00:01:08,318
<i>I picture you in my heart every day </i>

18
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:13,239
<i>Even today</i>
<i>You seep gently into my heart </i>

19
00:01:14,824 --> 00:01:18,244
<i>You are a gift </i>

20
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:21,539
<i>From the heavens </i>

21
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:24,667
<i>In this world where we stand alone </i>

22
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:29,547
<i>I'll keep you safe </i>

23
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:31,466
<i>Though you came to me </i>

24
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:37,222
<i>One day like a sudden shower </i>

25
00:01:37,305 --> 00:01:40,850
<i>I call out to you again today </i>

26
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:45,897
<i>You mean so much to me </i>

27
00:01:50,693 --> 00:01:53,863
TOUCHED

28
00:01:57,367 --> 00:02:00,203
RYU SUN-JAE JUST CAME BY
JAE-SEOK'S B&B

29
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:05,625
- All right, guys.
- Thank you.

30
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:08,503
Let's give it up for Woo-seok!

31
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:11,297
I can't believe it.

32
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:15,426
I never even imagined
I'd get to hear him sing that song live.

33
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:17,137
- Not for one second.
- Yeah, me neither.

34
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:21,683
Now that I've heard that, I don't need
to hear anything ever again.

35
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:24,602
That was insane!

36
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:27,397
- You were amazing.
- That was our very own Woo-seok.

37
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,524
- It was the best.
- Wasn't he great?

38
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:31,943
- Thank you.
- It was better because we sang together.

39
00:02:32,026 --> 00:02:34,487
My voice was shot.
I've been shouting too much.

40
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,239
Of course you'd say that.

41
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:38,908
Let's give it up for Ye-eun and Woo-seok,
one more time.

42
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:42,036
WOO-SEOK AND YE-EUN, THANK YOU
FOR YOUR SPECIAL PERFORMANCES

43
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:45,582
All right, everyone, we've been having
a blast with the campfire and everything.

44
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:48,001
- Kwang-soo!
- But now it's 9:15.

45
00:02:48,084 --> 00:02:50,253
- Oh, Kwang-soo? Yeah.
- What about our captain?

46
00:02:50,336 --> 00:02:52,213
- Oh, Kwang-soo? Yeah.
- No, sorry.

47
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:54,382
- I don't have anything to do. Seriously.
- You can do it.

48
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:55,967
- Mosquito dance!
- Mosquito.

49
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:58,636
They want to see the mosquito.

50
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:03,141
Kwang-soo, you gotta go. Do it.

51
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:05,143
Mosquito, mosquito, mosquito!

52
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:08,271
What do you mean, mosquito?
What are you talking about?

53
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,355
Listen, guys.

54
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:11,399
What do you mean, mosquito?

55
00:03:11,482 --> 00:03:13,276
Please sit down for a moment.

56
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:15,069
Let me get this straight.

57
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:18,239
You want Woo-seok and Ye-eun
to sing, but you're asking Kwang-soo to--

58
00:03:18,323 --> 00:03:19,532
FOR KWANG-SOO,
IT'S THE MOSQUITO DANCE

59
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:20,867
Mosquito.

60
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:22,327
What else did you expect?

61
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:24,829
- Mosquito.
- Kwang-soo, mosquito…

62
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:26,873
OH, MY SIDES

63
00:03:28,082 --> 00:03:29,959
HIT WITH REALITY

64
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:31,294
All right, now.

65
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:34,881
- Yes?
- You sing, Chief Yu.

66
00:03:34,964 --> 00:03:36,132
- Oh, me?
- Yes.

67
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:37,926
- Sing a song!
- Oh, my song?

68
00:03:38,009 --> 00:03:39,010
Sing a song!

69
00:03:39,093 --> 00:03:42,138
- Sing a song!
- I've got a ton of songs, but…

70
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:45,141
All right, then,
I'll just sing the first verse too.

71
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:46,643
Well, hang on. What should I sing?

72
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:48,645
I guess a trot song would be best, right?

73
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:50,772
- Sing Yusanseul!
- Let's see it!

74
00:03:50,855 --> 00:03:54,192
- Let's wrap things up with this song.
- Okay!

75
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:56,110
This stage was about everyone's talents,

76
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,947
and for some of you,
just plain showing off.

77
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:02,533
And in the end, all that's left
is Kwang-soo and the mosquito.

78
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:05,078
All right, guys,
let's bring tonight to a close.

79
00:04:05,161 --> 00:04:06,663
Thank you, everyone!

80
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,581
WITH JAE-SEOK'S PERFORMANCE
AS THE FINALE

81
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:13,878
"REDEVELOPMENT OF LOVE"
BY YUSANSEUL

82
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:25,473
<i>Please tear it all down </i>

83
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:26,849
Wow, he's good.

84
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:33,481
<i>From head to toe, every bit of it </i>

85
00:04:33,564 --> 00:04:39,237
<i>Please tear it all down </i>

86
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:44,659
<i>Not a single butterfly</i>
<i>Has flown into my heart </i>

87
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:48,454
<i>Please redevelop it </i>

88
00:04:50,498 --> 00:04:51,666
It felt like playing.

89
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:55,044
Like we were just hanging out
and the stage just happened to be there.

90
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:58,381
We really just had the time of our lives.

91
00:04:58,464 --> 00:05:01,384
It feels like we've left behind
all of our stress here.

92
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:04,554
I was truly laughing the whole time.

93
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:09,142
That moment, you could feel
everyone's good vibes coming together

94
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:12,020
and it created a fantastic atmosphere.

95
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:16,899
<i>Oh, if I plant Your affection in my heart</i>

96
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,192
<i>It will… </i>

97
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:19,819
God, I can't believe it. Too good.

98
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:21,904
THE PLOT-TWIST COUPLE
IS FULLY HYPED UP

99
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:25,950
<i>Beans would sprout </i>

100
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:31,706
<i>Please tear it all down completely </i>

101
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:37,170
<i>Not a single butterfly</i>
<i>Flew in my heart </i>

102
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:41,883
<i>Please redevelop it </i>

103
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:52,935
<i>Redevelopment of love </i>

104
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:54,437
All right, thank you!

105
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:56,564
We'll wrap it up there.

106
00:05:56,647 --> 00:05:57,857
Have a good night.

107
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:59,442
END OF THE TALENT SHOW

108
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:02,528
Oh, right, right. We've got
one last thing on today's schedule.

109
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:05,782
We asked you all to bring
a gift worth 30,000 won or less.

110
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:08,409
- Right?
- Yes.

111
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:10,453
It's nothing fancy,

112
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:13,790
but we thought it'd be nice to exchange
small gifts worth 30,000 won or less.

113
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:17,293
It's something nostalgic that a lot of us
remember doing when we were younger,

114
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:18,503
back in school.

115
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:21,214
It reminds us that community
is what keeps us going,

116
00:06:21,297 --> 00:06:24,926
and that the world can still be
a warm place if we choose to make it one.

117
00:06:25,009 --> 00:06:29,430
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES! NOTICE
THERE WILL BE A GIFT EXCHANGE

118
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:32,600
I got my gift. Can I put it
in your bag so no one will see it?

119
00:06:32,683 --> 00:06:35,937
- It's my gift.
- His gift. Look how he's holding it.

120
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:37,063
Did you bring a gift?

121
00:06:37,146 --> 00:06:39,732
- I can't wait to see what people brought.
- Right, I want to open them.

122
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:42,527
Let's collect the gifts now.

123
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:45,279
- Who's getting whose?
- It's gonna be random.

124
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:47,782
Put all your gifts in here
so no one can see them.

125
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:53,955
ONCE ALL THE GIFTS ARE COLLECTED

126
00:06:54,038 --> 00:06:56,040
That's big for something worth 30,000 won.

127
00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:57,125
A WHOLE LOT OF GIFTS

128
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,626
We put ours in there too.

129
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:02,046
Here, congratulations.

130
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:04,215
- Thank you.
- Here's your gift.

131
00:07:04,298 --> 00:07:06,217
- Here and here.
- Oh, wow.

132
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,593
- Thanks so much.
- Thank you.

133
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:08,970
- Here.
- That's mine.

134
00:07:09,053 --> 00:07:11,013
- Look.
- Thank you.

135
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,432
Oh, it's heavy.

136
00:07:12,515 --> 00:07:14,016
CURIOUS

137
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,893
What is it? It's big.

138
00:07:16,477 --> 00:07:19,772
Okay, now that everyone's got a gift,
let's open them up. Okay?

139
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:21,357
EXCITING RANDOM GIFT UNBOXING

140
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,109
- This is fun.
- Yeah.

141
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:24,485
EXCITED

142
00:07:25,069 --> 00:07:26,070
CURIOUS

143
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:28,573
- That's mine.
- It's from Jun-hyuk.

144
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:30,867
RUSTLING

145
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,702
- This is Jun-seong's.
- It's from Jun-seong.

146
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,162
Oh, really?

147
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:37,540
SNORT

148
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,253
FLUSTERED

149
00:07:42,837 --> 00:07:45,006
WHAT'S THAT?

150
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:48,843
- I'm confused.
- It's scary.

151
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:50,887
It's actually really detailed.

152
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:53,222
- Well, okay. Gosh. This is…
- It's so scary.

153
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:55,475
- I don't… I don't know what to say.
- It looks scary.

154
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:56,559
REACTION FAILURE

155
00:07:56,642 --> 00:07:58,519
That's from me.

156
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:00,688
- It's from me.
- It's cute.

157
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:03,316
- It's called a Cabbage Patch Kid.
- Okay.

158
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:05,860
It's a famous doll among vintage fans.

159
00:08:05,943 --> 00:08:07,069
Oh, really?

160
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:08,571
- Yeah, it's vintage.
- Yeah.

161
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:10,406
So, she wrote here,

162
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:13,034
"I hope this gift goes to a woman."

163
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:15,745
- As I always say…
- Na-eun might like it.

164
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:17,788
- …that's the fun of random gifts.
- Exactly.

165
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,958
- Kyo-young?
- I got this beautiful frame.

166
00:08:21,542 --> 00:08:24,921
And it came with a little card.

167
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:28,591
"I hope the little moments you shared here
stay with you for a long time.

168
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:31,677
I hope this frame reminds you
of all the beautiful memories,

169
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:34,597
- laughter and conversations you had here."
- Aw.

170
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:37,892
"And when everyday life gets tiring,
I hope looking at the photos

171
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:40,603
in this frame brings you a little comfort.

172
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:42,897
Thanks to you, I was truly happy.

173
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:45,107
Thank you. From Byeon Woo-seok."

174
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:49,362
Since we took so many photos,
I thought you could keep them in there.

175
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:50,530
Thank you so much.

176
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:52,448
I'll print them out
and put it in the frame.

177
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:53,866
That's really nice.

178
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,618
- She loves it.
- Yeah, I know.

179
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:58,037
All right, so who's next?

180
00:08:58,829 --> 00:08:59,914
WHAT DID EUN-TAE GET?

181
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,874
- Cute.
- It's really cute.

182
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,501
- It suits him.
- I love it.

183
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:05,962
- That's so cute.
- It should be your good-luck charm.

184
00:09:06,045 --> 00:09:08,839
- Actually, the card's even better.
- What's it say?

185
00:09:08,923 --> 00:09:11,008
"To the person receiving this gift,

186
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:15,930
when you're having a hard time,
when you're feeling worn out,

187
00:09:16,013 --> 00:09:18,891
or when you want to talk to someone,
try talking to this doll.

188
00:09:18,975 --> 00:09:20,184
I'm sure it'll help.

189
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:24,438
It'll tell you not to worry, not to waver,

190
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:27,066
and that you're right, because you are."

191
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:29,694
- Aw.
- Who's it from?

192
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:31,487
- It's so well-written.
- It's touching.

193
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,906
- Who wrote such a nice card?
- I feel like I'm going to cry.

194
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:36,033
Wow, that's really…

195
00:09:36,117 --> 00:09:38,995
- Who is it?
- Who is it?

196
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:43,291
It's me.

197
00:09:43,874 --> 00:09:45,084
I knew it.

198
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:47,003
It made me choke up a little, actually.

199
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:49,463
Oh, really?
I think it went to the right person.

200
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:50,881
It's very touching.

201
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:53,676
Eun-tae.

202
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,177
What did you get, Bo-ra?

203
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,096
I also got a gift that I really needed.

204
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:58,347
A tumbler.

205
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:00,474
- Now, the card's kind of long.
- Who's it from?

206
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:03,728
- They wrote a lot.
- They filled up both sides.

207
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:05,479
- And it's really touching.
- Who wrote it?

208
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:08,107
- I just read it and I'm kind of--
- Please read it to us.

209
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:10,693
"Hello, this is Lee Kwang-soo.

210
00:10:12,194 --> 00:10:15,156
They say even the briefest glance
can become a connection

211
00:10:15,239 --> 00:10:18,618
and I'm so grateful we were able
to share one so strong.

212
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:20,786
Did you enjoy your three days at the B&B?

213
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:24,248
It was exhausting for me, but I was
happy in such a simple, carefree way

214
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:25,916
that I'd do it all again.

215
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,837
I think I'll hold on to these
precious memories for a very long time.

216
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:33,090
After sharing so much time together,
I hope you will too.

217
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:35,217
I'll be cheering you on
as you continue your path,

218
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,345
and I hope that when things get tough,

219
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:39,805
these memories will bring a small smile…

220
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:41,849
bring a small smile to your face.

221
00:10:41,932 --> 00:10:44,685
From Staff Member Lee Kwang-soo."

222
00:10:45,353 --> 00:10:47,480
Why would you make her cry?

223
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:50,358
It was just that it felt so heartfelt.

224
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,817
- I really mean it.
- Thank you.

225
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:52,985
Right.

226
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:55,529
Theirs are all so meaningful. It's great.

227
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:57,239
"Our stay may have come to an end,

228
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:59,784
- but I hope our adventures continue."
- Wow!

229
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:02,870
It's from my fellow teammate.
The one and only Bo-ra gave it to me.

230
00:11:02,953 --> 00:11:05,498
- Her photo?
- Yeah, a photo of her.

231
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:07,667
She's a real nutcase.

232
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,502
I got nine pairs of socks.

233
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:11,962
- A fork.
- Oh, that's pretty!

234
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,047
That's really cute.

235
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:15,383
I got a camera.

236
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:17,051
- Wow.
- They're so cute.

237
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:18,678
FROM YE-EUN TO AE-YEONG:
WINE GLASSES

238
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:19,804
RANDOM GIFT EXCHANGE COMPLETE

239
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:21,472
- The notes were so sweet.
- They were so thoughtful.

240
00:11:21,555 --> 00:11:24,225
- This is so heartwarming. I love it.
- Agreed.

241
00:11:24,308 --> 00:11:28,312
By the way, some people told me earlier
that they have to leave early tomorrow.

242
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:30,398
- At 5:00 a.m.
- Oh, really?

243
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:32,692
Yeah, it's the three guys
who are taking a trip.

244
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:33,859
Aw.

245
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:35,695
- We'll be taking off.
- Well, it's a shame.

246
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:37,405
That's why they were so sad.

247
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:38,739
- Wait, why?
- Because they're ministers.

248
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:41,992
- It's Sunday.
- Right, that's true. It is Sunday.

249
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:44,203
SUNDAY IS CHURCH DAY

250
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:48,124
They want to say goodbye to you now

251
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:51,669
because while some of you might wake up
early, some of you might still be asleep.

252
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:54,714
- Go ahead, guys.
- Okay, well, I had a great time,

253
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:57,341
and now that it's actually the last day,
I'm sad to leave you all.

254
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:58,634
So are we.

255
00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:02,054
Hey, Dong-geon, look over there.

256
00:12:03,347 --> 00:12:05,808
I hope this didn't make things
worse between you two.

257
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:08,394
- We're always like this.
- Yeah.

258
00:12:08,477 --> 00:12:10,479
- I think we got closer.
- Oh, really?

259
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:11,814
I think they got closer.

260
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:13,816
This is the closest we've been in a while.

261
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:15,484
THIS MORNING, THEY WERE
ON COMPLETE OPPOSITE SIDES

262
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,945
- We got a little closer.
- Yeah, they're closer.

263
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:19,697
They've closed the gap by half.

264
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:22,825
Because they were both laughing a lot
at one another on stage.

265
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:25,161
THE JI SIBLINGS GOT
A LITTLE CLOSER AT THE B&B

266
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:26,954
THE LAST NIGHT DEEPENS

267
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:28,038
- Are you gonna cry?
- Bye.

268
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:30,583
- Take care.
- Thank you so much.

269
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:32,626
- I really had so much fun.
- Me too. I had a great time.

270
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:35,004
- Thanks for everything.
- Thank you.

271
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:37,715
- Thanks so much, really.
- We'll miss you guys.

272
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:40,384
Thanks for always being
so great to talk to.

273
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:41,886
We'll come see you.

274
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:43,304
Thank you so much.

275
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:48,142
Oh, no. No.

276
00:12:48,225 --> 00:12:50,352
- Don't cry.
- It's okay.

277
00:12:50,436 --> 00:12:51,479
Aw, don't cry.

278
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:53,522
- Why is he crying?
- Where's he going?

279
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:55,733
WOO-SEOK IS OVERWHELMED
WITH EMOTION

280
00:13:03,657 --> 00:13:06,076
Over the course of our time here,

281
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,121
I really felt the kindness and support.

282
00:13:09,205 --> 00:13:12,917
The way they looked at me,
all the love that they showed…

283
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:17,046
I knew when the time came to say goodbye,
I was going to want to thank people.

284
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,715
And the moment I actually
went up to say thank you,

285
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:22,676
all these emotions just kind of exploded.

286
00:13:29,058 --> 00:13:31,268
TEARS BROKE OUT
AS THE FAREWELL APPROACHED

287
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:35,105
I feel like time went by so quickly,
and that makes me a little sad.

288
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:37,066
It'll be a great memory.

289
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,735
I think I would want to come back too.

290
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:42,988
WOO-SEOK CHERISHED EVERY MOMENT

291
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:45,491
I could feel that
the guests truly cherished

292
00:13:45,574 --> 00:13:47,535
every moment we spent together.

293
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:50,871
They seemed happy
and seeing that brought me pride

294
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:53,749
and made me feel incredibly happy too.

295
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:57,044
I've never felt like this before
and I know it's a memory

296
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:59,672
I'll think back on a lot
when things get tough.

297
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:02,299
It'll just come to me out of the blue.

298
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:06,595
- Are you all right?
- Oh, I'm fine.

299
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:08,222
TEAM WOO-SEOK FOLLOWS HIM IN

300
00:14:08,305 --> 00:14:10,516
Over these three days and two nights,

301
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:14,436
I feel like I'm the one who got
to recharge, thanks to all of you.

302
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:16,856
I really do feel so grateful to you all.

303
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:22,111
Man, I feel so silly.
I never imagined I'd cry.

304
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:27,992
HIS HYUNGS FOLLOW HIM IN

305
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,827
Woo-seok's feeling it.

306
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:32,079
Woo-seok, we're heading upstairs.

307
00:14:32,162 --> 00:14:33,163
Okay.

308
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:34,915
- When you're done--
- Go ahead.

309
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:36,166
No. Please, just go.

310
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,335
Okay, fine. Geez.

311
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:41,672
GOT KICKED OUT

312
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:47,219
Why are you filming him?

313
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:48,304
KWANG-SOO CAM ON

314
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:49,471
Do you mind not filming?

315
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:52,141
BYEON WOO-SEOK CAUGHT CRYING

316
00:14:53,183 --> 00:14:54,727
We all feel the same.

317
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:59,648
So it really doesn't matter
how long you've spent with someone.

318
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,358
UP-CLOSE COVERAGE

319
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:05,321
I meet all kinds of people at work,
and some of them are not so nice.

320
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,031
Keep going. Don't mind me.

321
00:15:07,114 --> 00:15:08,782
It's kind of hard
with a camera in my face.

322
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:11,118
- No, just cry. Go ahead. It's okay.
- I'm not crying.

323
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:12,786
I'm not. I've totally calmed down.

324
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:17,750
LEAVING
AFTER COMPLETING HIS MISSION

325
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:20,669
Yeah, I'm gonna run away now. Bye.

326
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:21,754
SUDDENLY EMBARRASSED

327
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:25,716
WOO-SEOK RAN
STRAIGHT BACK TO HIS ROOM

328
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:28,469
- Ye-eun.
- Yes?

329
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:30,262
Aw.

330
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,807
Please don't tell anyone about this.

331
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:35,726
Oppa.

332
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:37,436
EMBARRASSED

333
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:40,981
I just wanted to say thank you
for everything, but I ended up crying.

334
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:42,066
Anyway.

335
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:43,901
- Oppa.
- Yeah?

336
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:45,653
So sad.

337
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:50,491
<i>Everyone, thank you so much</i>
<i>for all your hard work today.</i>

338
00:15:50,574 --> 00:15:55,079
Thanks to you, it was another fun,
happy, and fulfilling day.

339
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:57,289
All right, see you tomorrow morning.

340
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:58,874
- Okay!
- Bye.

341
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:00,417
Bye!

342
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:01,502
Good night.

343
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:02,920
Good night!

344
00:16:11,261 --> 00:16:14,139
THE DOOR BROTHERS
ON LIGHTS-OUT DUTY

345
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:19,269
GROUP 1'S LAST NIGHT
AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

346
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:24,858
GYMNASIUM
4:35 A.M.

347
00:16:26,193 --> 00:16:28,988
WIGGLING

348
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:33,659
DONG-GEON WAKES UP
EARLY IN THE MORNING

349
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:36,870
We have to get up.

350
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:39,581
MINISTER SEONG-JOON IS UP

351
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,960
MINISTER HYO-JUNG IS UP TOO

352
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,546
TIPTOEING

353
00:16:45,629 --> 00:16:46,672
Who's up?

354
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:50,050
SOMEONE ELSE IS UP THIS EARLY?

355
00:16:50,634 --> 00:16:52,469
- It's cold. Stay in bed.
- Oh.

356
00:16:54,471 --> 00:16:56,557
- Let me get changed quickly.
- Of course, take your time.

357
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:58,642
CHIEF YU WOKE UP EARLY
TO SEE THEM OFF

358
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:05,441
Wow, Minister.

359
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:07,192
He looks different in a suit.

360
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:11,864
How are you getting there?

361
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:14,616
We're gonna drive there
together in our car.

362
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,910
I'll drive you
down to the parking lot, then.

363
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:19,496
JAE-SEOK WANTS TO DRIVE THEM
DOWN TO THE PARKING LOT

364
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,665
That's where the closing ceremony will be.

365
00:17:21,749 --> 00:17:24,001
- Yeah?
- You three want to do it?

366
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:29,381
- Thanks for everything.
- I'm really grateful for this.

367
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:32,885
- Minister.
- Thank you. Thanks for everything.

368
00:17:32,968 --> 00:17:34,303
Thank you.

369
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:36,555
- Congrats on the wedding.
- Thanks.

370
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:39,433
- Are you going straight to church?
- Yeah.

371
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:41,643
Boy, you'll be tired.

372
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:44,521
- Not as tired as you.
- No, no, no.

373
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:47,399
- Thank you again. For everything.
- No need to thank me.

374
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:48,817
SEONG-JOON, HYO-JUNG,
AND DONG-GEON CHECK OUT

375
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:52,446
HIS SISTER'S OBLIVIOUSLY ASLEEP

376
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,239
CURRENT TIME
7:00 A.M.

377
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:55,657
God.

378
00:17:58,035 --> 00:18:00,537
EVERYONE'S UP
EARLY IN THE MORNING

379
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,623
Uh, my voice.

380
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:05,375
- Oh, I'm so tired.
- This is how my voice sounds now.

381
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:11,173
ALL THEY CAN DO
IS LOOK AT EACH OTHER AND LAUGH

382
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:13,342
FIRST DAY AT THE B&B

383
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:14,885
DAY 3 OF OPERATIONS

384
00:18:14,968 --> 00:18:18,388
<i>Introducing our next</i>
<i>staff member, Mr. Byeon Woo-seok.</i>

385
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:19,973
FRESH

386
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:21,642
WORN OUT

387
00:18:21,725 --> 00:18:24,895
A TOTAL WRECK

388
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,606
Geez.

389
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:31,026
I shouted too much last night.

390
00:18:31,527 --> 00:18:34,279
CHIEF YU'S VOICE IS SHOT

391
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:36,031
TIME TO GET MOVING

392
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:38,158
1. A JACKET OVER PAJAMAS

393
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,536
2. COMBING IS A LUXURY

394
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:42,746
3. BRUSHING TEETH

395
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,873
NO BRUSHING TEETH

396
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:47,126
HIT WITH REALITY

397
00:18:51,213 --> 00:18:52,714
4. CAP PULLED LOW DOWN

398
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:54,883
WHY DID THEY START GETTING READY
SO EARLY IN THE MORNING?

399
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:58,679
I want to give them a hearty breakfast.
It's their last meal.

400
00:18:58,762 --> 00:19:00,472
I think gomtang would be perfect for them.

401
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:02,015
Gomtang. Gomtang.

402
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:05,519
Yeah, we can call them now and then
we'll go pick it up in the morning.

403
00:19:05,602 --> 00:19:08,355
It's been a long time
since I had a morning like this.

404
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:11,400
- You know, this weather…
- Morning air, huh?

405
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:13,110
Yeah. Man, it's cold.

406
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:16,446
YESTERDAY FELT LIKE EARLY FALL
WITH A HIGH OF 20°C

407
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:19,700
OVERNIGHT, THE TEMPERATURE
PLUNGED TO A LOW OF 10°C

408
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:22,536
Hyung, you were hilarious last night.

409
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:27,833
When you got into bed, you were like…

410
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:29,168
I passed out?

411
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:31,378
WITH A SIGH,
HE DRIFTED INTO A DEEP SLEEP

412
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:33,881
Yeah, when I heard him
snore the first night,

413
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:36,592
I was like,
"Wow, he must be really tired."

414
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:38,468
- But this was next level.
- Yeah, it was.

415
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,888
Last night was completely different.

416
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:42,431
THE 1ST NIGHT AT THE B&B

417
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:44,600
ZZZ FROM NORMAL SNORING

418
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:46,351
THE 2ND NIGHT AT THE B&B

419
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:48,437
ZZZ UPGRADED
TO THE CAREFREE VERSION

420
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,355
My whole body feels like lead.

421
00:19:50,981 --> 00:19:51,982
This must be it.

422
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:53,817
DRAGGING THEIR WEARY BODIES,
THEY ARRIVE AT THE GOMTANG PLACE

423
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,152
- It's already packed.
- Right.

424
00:19:55,235 --> 00:19:57,571
- Thank you. Have a good day.
- Thank you. Have a good one.

425
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,240
OFF TO HEAT UP THE GOMTANG

426
00:20:00,324 --> 00:20:02,242
- Okay, we're here.
- To the kitchen.

427
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:03,952
Straight to the kitchen.

428
00:20:05,954 --> 00:20:07,581
- Should I just pour it in?
- Yeah.

429
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:12,544
- So, breakfast at 8:40?
- Yeah.

430
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:14,755
Then I'm going to go get ready.
I'll be back in a minute.

431
00:20:14,838 --> 00:20:15,839
Okay.

432
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:17,925
That scared me.

433
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:19,635
CURRENT TIME
8:00 A.M.

434
00:20:19,718 --> 00:20:21,511
GOOD MORNING

435
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:23,555
Uh-oh. He's at the mic.

436
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:25,641
BOUNCE, BOUNCE

437
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:30,229
All right, everyone, good morning.

438
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:32,272
<i>Did you sleep well?</i>

439
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:34,149
- Yes!
- Yes!

440
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:36,235
- <i>All right.</i>
- Listen to Jae-seok's voice.

441
00:20:36,318 --> 00:20:38,028
It's totally gone, huh?

442
00:20:38,111 --> 00:20:40,697
<i>Finally it's the morning</i>

443
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:44,076
<i>of day three, the last day.</i>

444
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:45,953
His voice is shot.

445
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:47,412
It's our third day.

446
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:48,747
Did you sleep well?

447
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:50,374
- Yes!
- Yes!

448
00:20:50,457 --> 00:20:55,379
We'll be meeting downstairs in the dining
area to have breakfast at 8:40.

449
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:57,965
- I'll see you in a bit.
- Okay.

450
00:20:58,548 --> 00:20:59,549
Aren't you cold?

451
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:00,884
- No.
- No.

452
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:02,719
BY DAY 3 THE GUESTS KNOW
TO TURN THE LIGHTS ON

453
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:05,764
- Whoa, that's manual?
- Yeah, we do it by hand.

454
00:21:05,847 --> 00:21:08,308
Here comes the sun.

455
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:09,434
100% MANUAL SUNRISE

456
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:10,560
All right!

457
00:21:10,644 --> 00:21:13,814
Last night's talent show
took it out of me.

458
00:21:13,897 --> 00:21:15,565
- I shouted too much.
- You shouted too much.

459
00:21:15,649 --> 00:21:16,650
Oh, no.

460
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:21,822
WHILE THE GOMTANG HEATS UP,
THE STAFF FRESHENS UP

461
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:26,618
I've got to brush my teeth too.

462
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:27,911
SHOWS UP
WITH HIS T-SHIRT TUCKED IN

463
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:33,792
A QUICK HAIR WASH

464
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:40,924
Oh, it's cold.

465
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:46,054
Why isn't this working?

466
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:48,515
THE GUESTS FRESHEN UP TOO

467
00:21:48,598 --> 00:21:50,183
Last look at the waterfall.

468
00:21:51,393 --> 00:21:54,229
EACH GUEST ENJOYS FREE TIME
IN THEIR OWN WAY

469
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:57,816
CURRENT TIME
8:40 A.M.

470
00:21:57,899 --> 00:21:59,484
The gomtang smells good.

471
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:03,447
I knew this would be perfect
for us to have as the last breakfast.

472
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:04,781
Everything's perfect.

473
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:05,866
THE MEAL PREP IS PERFECT TOO

474
00:22:05,949 --> 00:22:08,160
- They're coming. They're coming.
- Get in position.

475
00:22:08,243 --> 00:22:09,870
- Gomtang?
- Gomtang?

476
00:22:09,953 --> 00:22:10,954
Gomtang?

477
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:15,959
- Gomtang's the best breakfast.
- Absolutely.

478
00:22:16,043 --> 00:22:18,754
- You get the meat and I'll get the broth.
- This is too much.

479
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:21,882
- Lots of protein for the detective.
- Yeah, thank you.

480
00:22:21,965 --> 00:22:23,550
- Thank you for the food.
- There you go.

481
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:24,634
PLENTY

482
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:27,512
- This is a lot of meat.
- Help yourself.

483
00:22:27,596 --> 00:22:29,598
- It's a reward for your great dancing.
- That's right.

484
00:22:29,681 --> 00:22:31,933
- Oh, really? Thank you.
- Thank you.

485
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:33,894
- Help yourself.
- Enjoy.

486
00:22:33,977 --> 00:22:36,480
- This'll warm me up. I'm so cold.
- This is great.

487
00:22:38,815 --> 00:22:40,734
- Good, right?
- It's amazing.

488
00:22:44,237 --> 00:22:45,739
How's the gomtang?

489
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:47,407
- Great job!
- So good.

490
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:48,992
It's a winner.

491
00:22:51,661 --> 00:22:53,330
The gomtang is really good.

492
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:58,377
- Great choice.
- This is delicious.

493
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:01,129
- It was a great choice, Hyung.
- Seriously.

494
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,547
This hits the spot.

495
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:06,218
A SATISFYING MEAL
AND GREAT WEATHER

496
00:23:06,301 --> 00:23:08,220
- Wow, I'm so full.
- That was great.

497
00:23:08,303 --> 00:23:09,638
THE GUEST IS KING, AND SO AM I

498
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:11,598
We should start packing now.

499
00:23:11,681 --> 00:23:14,226
- I don't want to leave.
- Me neither.

500
00:23:14,309 --> 00:23:15,602
It's a bummer.

501
00:23:15,685 --> 00:23:18,688
- I know. It is.
- It really is, Chief Yu.

502
00:23:18,772 --> 00:23:22,192
Tomorrow this will all feel
like it was just a dream.

503
00:23:22,275 --> 00:23:23,693
Yeah, just a dream.

504
00:23:24,903 --> 00:23:28,115
I wish they kept this place here so
we could come back in a couple of months.

505
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:29,699
- I'd love that.
- I know, right?

506
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:31,618
SETTING ASIDE
THEIR LINGERING WISTFULNESS

507
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:33,286
THE GUESTS GET READY
TO CHECK OUT

508
00:23:33,870 --> 00:23:35,414
We're really leaving.

509
00:23:35,997 --> 00:23:38,375
- I think this'll be a nice gift.
- It'll be a great gift.

510
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:41,002
A memento. It feels good to get an award.

511
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:42,629
- Definitely.
- Of course.

512
00:23:42,712 --> 00:23:44,965
And this is an award
I'm sure they never saw coming.

513
00:23:45,048 --> 00:23:47,092
- They're all winners.
- Everyone's good at something.

514
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:48,677
Everyone has something to brag about.

515
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,304
We'll now have a closing ceremony outside.

516
00:23:51,388 --> 00:23:52,681
- Aw.
- Okay!

517
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:53,974
Everyone, let's move.

518
00:23:54,057 --> 00:23:55,058
All right, everyone.

519
00:23:55,142 --> 00:23:57,477
We've completed our full two-night,
three-day schedule

520
00:23:57,561 --> 00:23:59,729
and now it's finally time
for the closing ceremony.

521
00:23:59,813 --> 00:24:00,814
Aw.

522
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:03,567
We are now going to announce
the MVP guests

523
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:06,445
and present them
with their award certificates.

524
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:08,572
What an honor.

525
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:12,826
Actual certificates!

526
00:24:12,909 --> 00:24:14,661
- This is so official.
- Awesome.

527
00:24:14,744 --> 00:24:18,039
All right,
please congratulate our MVP guests

528
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:20,041
with a big round of applause.

529
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:23,962
<i>Jae-seok's B&B's Rules,</i>
the Three Beautiful Angels Award.

530
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:27,382
Son Hyeong-seon, Ko Eun-jung,
and Lee Ae-yeong.

531
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:30,844
All right. "These three people

532
00:24:30,927 --> 00:24:33,472
with their angelic hearts and positivity,

533
00:24:33,555 --> 00:24:36,141
brought warmth to everyone
at Jae-seok's B&B."

534
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:37,309
Absolutely.

535
00:24:37,392 --> 00:24:38,643
So we present them with this award.

536
00:24:38,727 --> 00:24:41,062
From all of us on the B&B staff,
congratulations.

537
00:24:41,146 --> 00:24:42,772
They made this so fun.

538
00:24:43,940 --> 00:24:46,735
FROM A PASSIONATE TALENT SHOW/
SHOWING OFF PERFORMANCE

539
00:24:48,236 --> 00:24:50,614
- We're your big sisters.
- You guys are on another level.

540
00:24:50,697 --> 00:24:51,948
Then I saw the coffee machine.

541
00:24:52,032 --> 00:24:53,617
TO BEING
THE GUESTS' EMPATHY FAIRIES

542
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:56,870
We're on vacation.
Why are we crying thinking about our kids?

543
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:00,916
Thank you.

544
00:25:01,541 --> 00:25:02,792
Congratulations.

545
00:25:02,876 --> 00:25:04,961
Thank you. Thank you.

546
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:06,588
- Too sweet.
- Oh, what is this?

547
00:25:06,671 --> 00:25:08,256
Oh, wow.

548
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,549
Here.

549
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:10,800
We're always crying.

550
00:25:11,426 --> 00:25:12,594
Oh, my gosh.

551
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:14,721
Congrats.

552
00:25:14,804 --> 00:25:16,181
Don't cry.

553
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:19,059
- I'm gonna cry.
- Me too.

554
00:25:19,142 --> 00:25:21,019
Oh, no. Here come the water works.

555
00:25:21,978 --> 00:25:23,563
They're crying.

556
00:25:23,647 --> 00:25:25,732
The Three Beautiful Angels.

557
00:25:25,815 --> 00:25:28,360
Once you go back to your everyday lives,

558
00:25:28,443 --> 00:25:31,112
you'll be busy again,
taking care of your families

559
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:34,324
and I know it won't be easy,
but during your stay here,

560
00:25:34,407 --> 00:25:37,118
you set everything aside
and showed us who you truly are,

561
00:25:37,202 --> 00:25:40,580
and for that I want to sincerely
thank you once again.

562
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:42,374
Go, Three Angels!

563
00:25:43,166 --> 00:25:44,960
- My sincere congratulations.
- Congratulations.

564
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:46,253
Thank you.

565
00:25:46,336 --> 00:25:48,797
All right. There's more.

566
00:25:49,589 --> 00:25:51,508
- Oh?
- Oh?

567
00:25:51,591 --> 00:25:54,761
All right.
The next award is the Hot Girl Award.

568
00:25:56,012 --> 00:25:57,097
- Hot girl?
- Yes.

569
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:59,558
The Hot Girl Award goes to Kim Joo-hyun.

570
00:26:02,894 --> 00:26:06,356
Okay, Joo-hyun. Wait…
Wait till you hear what it's for.

571
00:26:06,439 --> 00:26:07,732
Not that kind of hot.

572
00:26:07,816 --> 00:26:10,652
"Despite the chilly autumn weather
here at Jae-seok's B&B…"

573
00:26:10,735 --> 00:26:12,988
Oh, that kind of hot.

574
00:26:13,071 --> 00:26:17,617
"…she showed her fiery, hot girl side
by rocking short sleeves and shorts.

575
00:26:17,701 --> 00:26:20,829
So we present her with this award.
Congratulations."

576
00:26:20,912 --> 00:26:22,163
Paparazzi, paparazzi, paparazzi.

577
00:26:22,247 --> 00:26:23,248
THE "PAPARAZZI" HOT GIRL

578
00:26:24,666 --> 00:26:29,713
The Most Surprising Couple Award
goes to Park Kyo-young and Yeo Dong-kyu.

579
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:32,757
Five, six, seven, eight.

580
00:26:35,844 --> 00:26:38,305
IN THE ZONE

581
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:42,475
I mean, what the heck is that?

582
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:45,478
All right,
let's move on to the next award.

583
00:26:45,562 --> 00:26:47,022
Wait, there are more?

584
00:26:47,105 --> 00:26:48,356
This award is perfect for him.

585
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,108
The Foodie Award goes to Lee Jae-seong.

586
00:26:50,191 --> 00:26:51,192
Agreed!

587
00:26:51,276 --> 00:26:53,111
The Hip Award. The Fantastic Dancer Award.

588
00:26:53,194 --> 00:26:54,446
So talented.

589
00:26:55,322 --> 00:26:57,991
Chef Award, Eldest Daughter Award,
Change My Sisters Award.

590
00:26:58,074 --> 00:26:59,701
MIRACLE MORNING AWARD, SET ME UP
AWARD, POCKET BOY AWARD

591
00:26:59,784 --> 00:27:02,037
- Congratulations.
- Everyone gets one.

592
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:05,081
All right, that wraps up
the MVP announcements

593
00:27:05,165 --> 00:27:06,916
and award presentations.

594
00:27:07,626 --> 00:27:11,004
We actually put together
one more award at the last minute.

595
00:27:11,755 --> 00:27:13,340
That award is…

596
00:27:13,923 --> 00:27:15,091
Here we go.

597
00:27:15,175 --> 00:27:16,968
…the Best…

598
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:19,679
Mosquito Award, Lee Kwang-soo.

599
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:21,681
BEST MOSQUITO AWARD
LEE KWANG-SOO

600
00:27:21,765 --> 00:27:23,224
What?

601
00:27:23,308 --> 00:27:26,061
- All right. This award…
- Mosquito! Mosquito! Mosquito!

602
00:27:26,144 --> 00:27:27,771
Best Mosquito Award?

603
00:27:27,854 --> 00:27:30,231
"This person earned
a new nickname every day,

604
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:32,442
like the Earring Prince and Mosquito.

605
00:27:32,525 --> 00:27:36,029
And sucked the laughs
out of our guests like a mosquito.

606
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,656
So we present him with this award."

607
00:27:37,739 --> 00:27:39,240
- I'm jealous.
- I'm so jealous.

608
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:40,909
- Come get your award.
- Thank you.

609
00:27:40,992 --> 00:27:42,410
NOT THRILLED

610
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:46,039
- No speech. Just do the dance.
- The dance.

611
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:48,708
Show us the mosquito dance, please!

612
00:27:48,792 --> 00:27:52,671
- Mosquito! Mosquito!
- Mosquito! Mosquito!

613
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:55,173
<i>A huge mosquito bit my foot</i>
<i>It itched me so much </i>

614
00:27:55,256 --> 00:27:57,175
- <i>It itched me so much</i>
- <i>It itched so much </i>

615
00:27:57,258 --> 00:27:58,343
I LOVE IT

616
00:27:58,426 --> 00:27:59,844
SUDDENLY HIT WITH REALITY

617
00:27:59,928 --> 00:28:01,721
- You can do it!
- You've got this!

618
00:28:01,805 --> 00:28:03,181
- You got this!
- You can do it!

619
00:28:03,264 --> 00:28:04,599
Come on, dance.

620
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:07,394
<i>Without even thinking</i>
<i>I scratched my foot </i>

621
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:10,188
<i>Left with no choice</i>
<i>I made a cross with my fingernails </i>

622
00:28:11,147 --> 00:28:12,774
Congratulations.

623
00:28:13,983 --> 00:28:16,444
- Congrats.
- You're awesome!

624
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:18,738
That was great. We love you!

625
00:28:18,822 --> 00:28:20,323
I can't believe he did that.

626
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:22,367
LAUGHING

627
00:28:22,450 --> 00:28:24,619
- This is my first time seeing this part.
- Same.

628
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:26,996
I've never seen that mosquito pose.

629
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:29,874
I move on from embarrassment quickly.

630
00:28:29,958 --> 00:28:31,376
So I don't remember any of it.

631
00:28:31,459 --> 00:28:33,628
MEMORY LOSS

632
00:28:33,712 --> 00:28:39,050
All right, lastly, I'd like to say
a few final words to you all.

633
00:28:39,134 --> 00:28:42,429
Once you walk out
through those gates of Jae-seok's B&B,

634
00:28:42,512 --> 00:28:46,307
you'll be heading back to your own lives,
to the place where each of you belongs.

635
00:28:46,391 --> 00:28:49,185
No matter where you are,
even if things get hard

636
00:28:49,269 --> 00:28:52,689
or you feel worn down, and even
if you stumble and fall for a moment,

637
00:28:52,772 --> 00:28:54,315
never give up.

638
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:55,817
Win that fight.

639
00:28:55,900 --> 00:29:01,197
I truly hope that one day you achieve
everything you've been hoping for.

640
00:29:01,281 --> 00:29:03,867
It's been such a pleasure
being here with you.

641
00:29:03,950 --> 00:29:05,160
You made me so happy.

642
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:08,955
And lastly, you're all someone's precious
sons and daughters

643
00:29:09,038 --> 00:29:10,457
and it was truly an honor to host you.

644
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:11,541
Thank you.

645
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:14,919
- Thank you.
- We're so grateful.

646
00:29:15,003 --> 00:29:17,213
- Thank you.
- Thank you for everything.

647
00:29:18,965 --> 00:29:20,425
I was honestly pretty worried

648
00:29:20,508 --> 00:29:24,888
about spending three days and two nights,
with such a large group of people.

649
00:29:24,971 --> 00:29:28,349
It was something I'd never done before,
so I definitely had a lot of concerns.

650
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:30,935
But seeing how moved they were,
I'm really glad I did.

651
00:29:31,019 --> 00:29:33,188
I realized how much joy I could give them.

652
00:29:34,063 --> 00:29:36,566
- Thank you, Woo-seok.
- A pleasure.

653
00:29:36,649 --> 00:29:39,110
- Don't you start crying.
- You're the one who cried first.

654
00:29:41,112 --> 00:29:42,947
- Get home safe.
- This was amazing.

655
00:29:43,031 --> 00:29:44,783
- Thanks for everything.
- Get home safe.

656
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:46,409
- Bye, everybody. Take care.
- Bye.

657
00:29:46,493 --> 00:29:47,494
EXCHANGING BITTERSWEET GOODBYES

658
00:29:48,119 --> 00:29:49,871
And we're out. That's it.

659
00:29:49,954 --> 00:29:51,748
There's no coming back here now. Bye.

660
00:29:51,831 --> 00:29:54,292
I can't stop looking back.

661
00:29:56,211 --> 00:29:58,797
Chief Yu said something really great.

662
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:01,382
- "Everyone has their own crazy side."
- Crazy side.

663
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:04,552
- Yeah.
- I realized how true that was.

664
00:30:04,636 --> 00:30:06,054
Here at the B&B.

665
00:30:06,638 --> 00:30:09,682
The whole stay
just really felt like a gift.

666
00:30:09,766 --> 00:30:11,351
While I was here at the B&B,

667
00:30:11,434 --> 00:30:14,312
I honestly didn't think
about the real world at all.

668
00:30:14,395 --> 00:30:16,940
I didn't have
any of my worries or concerns.

669
00:30:17,023 --> 00:30:19,818
It was kind of awkward
between me and my sister,

670
00:30:19,901 --> 00:30:22,403
but I feel like we got closer here.

671
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:24,280
- Nice to meet you.
- Wait!

672
00:30:24,364 --> 00:30:28,201
Being here, I realized
that not everyone can do what she does.

673
00:30:28,284 --> 00:30:29,828
Let me see that.

674
00:30:30,411 --> 00:30:31,538
This is how we make it taste good.

675
00:30:31,621 --> 00:30:34,207
It was the first time
I truly wanted to support her

676
00:30:34,290 --> 00:30:36,918
and it made me respect her even more.

677
00:30:37,794 --> 00:30:40,004
I did get a little choked up there,

678
00:30:40,713 --> 00:30:42,423
even though I didn't say anything.

679
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:46,678
The truth is, when she cried last night,
it really hit me hard too.

680
00:30:46,761 --> 00:30:49,347
I've actually been
really worried about her,

681
00:30:49,430 --> 00:30:51,432
and have wanted to see that side of her,

682
00:30:51,516 --> 00:30:54,936
but she's never shown any of that
in front of the family.

683
00:30:55,019 --> 00:30:58,356
Seeing her enjoy herself
with everyone like this

684
00:30:58,439 --> 00:31:00,608
has made me really happy.

685
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:03,152
I'm just grateful
I got to have this experience.

686
00:31:03,236 --> 00:31:05,822
DAB, DAB

687
00:31:06,406 --> 00:31:09,742
- Get home safe.
- Bye.

688
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:13,204
- This is so sad.
- I think you're a little teary-eyed too.

689
00:31:13,288 --> 00:31:14,289
Well…

690
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:16,374
- You did great, Ye-eun.
- You too.

691
00:31:16,457 --> 00:31:17,750
- Good job.
- Great work, Woo-seok.

692
00:31:17,834 --> 00:31:19,002
- Good job.
- You too, Kwang-soo.

693
00:31:19,085 --> 00:31:22,463
When other people see this, they're
gonna say, "What's wrong with them?"

694
00:31:22,547 --> 00:31:24,173
They'd say it was a bit over the top.

695
00:31:24,257 --> 00:31:25,884
Yeah, over the top.

696
00:31:26,551 --> 00:31:29,304
All right, it's time to start
thinking about the next group.

697
00:31:29,387 --> 00:31:32,098
Every game goes through
a beta testing phase,

698
00:31:32,181 --> 00:31:34,475
and that's how the system
starts to come together.

699
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:37,103
I think we should stock up
on a lot more kimchi from the start.

700
00:31:37,186 --> 00:31:38,229
Yeah, I think we should.

701
00:31:38,313 --> 00:31:40,690
- It'll be too cold to go out in November.
- Yeah, too cold.

702
00:31:40,773 --> 00:31:43,943
I did think about asking
if anyone wanted to do a group workout.

703
00:31:44,027 --> 00:31:45,945
- I thought it might be fun.
- I had the same thought.

704
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:48,156
- All right, we'll leave it there for now.
- All right.

705
00:31:48,239 --> 00:31:50,199
- Good job, everyone.
- Great work.

706
00:31:50,283 --> 00:31:52,076
PREPARING THEMSELVES FOR GROUP 2

707
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:53,328
Captain.

708
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:58,249
ONE MONTH LATER

709
00:31:59,208 --> 00:32:01,794
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT, THE LEAVES
HAVE TURNED RED AND YELLOW

710
00:32:02,378 --> 00:32:05,048
IT'S LATE AUTUMN
AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

711
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:06,925
CURRENT TEMPERATURE
8°C

712
00:32:07,008 --> 00:32:10,136
Ah, my goodness.
It really feels like fall now.

713
00:32:10,219 --> 00:32:12,305
I know. It feels totally different.

714
00:32:12,388 --> 00:32:15,934
When the four of us met at first,
it didn't feel like this at all.

715
00:32:16,017 --> 00:32:17,936
- It was really warm.
- That's right.

716
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:20,772
And we've come prepared
with a lot more stuff now.

717
00:32:20,855 --> 00:32:22,732
- A lot more.
- Way more than last time.

718
00:32:22,815 --> 00:32:24,484
- Now we're prepared.
- I learned my lesson.

719
00:32:24,567 --> 00:32:26,402
It's nice being back after so long.

720
00:32:26,486 --> 00:32:27,695
It's changed.

721
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:31,991
Since it's getting colder, they went ahead
and put a roof on the workout area.

722
00:32:32,075 --> 00:32:33,409
Wow.

723
00:32:34,994 --> 00:32:37,705
THE OUTDOOR GYM

724
00:32:38,581 --> 00:32:41,793
HAS BEEN TURNED
INTO AN INDOOR GYM

725
00:32:41,876 --> 00:32:44,545
We've got a plastic enclosure
over the gym equipment now

726
00:32:44,629 --> 00:32:47,090
to keep it warm and comfortable
for everyone.

727
00:32:52,428 --> 00:32:53,846
It's amazing.

728
00:32:54,514 --> 00:32:57,016
- The gym feels so cozy now.
- Yeah, so cozy.

729
00:32:57,100 --> 00:32:58,893
We can close this when it gets cold.

730
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:01,437
I actually feel like working out here.

731
00:33:01,521 --> 00:33:03,481
- Yeah, it's nice.
- It's really nice.

732
00:33:03,564 --> 00:33:05,149
We've got this too.

733
00:33:06,401 --> 00:33:07,485
GRILLING STATION
WARMING CABINET

734
00:33:07,568 --> 00:33:08,569
SWEET POTATOES
STEAMED BUNS

735
00:33:09,612 --> 00:33:12,657
JAE-SEOK'S B&B HAS BEEN UPGRADED

736
00:33:12,740 --> 00:33:14,784
Honestly I kind of feel bad
for the first group,

737
00:33:14,867 --> 00:33:16,828
'cause this already feels
much more put together.

738
00:33:16,911 --> 00:33:18,830
- It's definitely gotten better.
- We've improved it.

739
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:20,081
Hold on.

740
00:33:20,164 --> 00:33:21,958
Let's put our stuff down here for now.

741
00:33:22,542 --> 00:33:23,543
Okay.

742
00:33:24,627 --> 00:33:27,630
- We have to make lunch now.
- Ugh, geez…

743
00:33:27,714 --> 00:33:28,798
It's warm in here.

744
00:33:28,881 --> 00:33:30,717
- I can't believe it.
- We have to make lunch.

745
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:32,969
- You should take off your earrings now.
- Yeah.

746
00:33:33,052 --> 00:33:36,431
By the way, after the first time
that we were all here together,

747
00:33:36,514 --> 00:33:38,808
I bought you a gift, Kwang-soo,
because I kept thinking about you.

748
00:33:38,891 --> 00:33:40,393
- What did you get?
- Wow.

749
00:33:41,185 --> 00:33:43,271
- Seriously?
- Yeah, I brought you a gift.

750
00:33:43,354 --> 00:33:44,772
I didn't bring you anything.

751
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:46,774
- I think I know what it is.
- What?

752
00:33:46,858 --> 00:33:48,693
Mosquito repellent?

753
00:33:48,776 --> 00:33:50,570
- Why would he get me that?
- It's not that.

754
00:33:50,653 --> 00:33:51,779
- It's useful.
- Don't start.

755
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:54,741
Well, I saw these and I thought
that they might look good on you.

756
00:33:54,824 --> 00:33:56,159
What is it?

757
00:33:56,242 --> 00:33:58,536
- A clip-on nose ring and a lip ring.
- Wow.

758
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:00,121
WHAT ARE THOSE?

759
00:34:00,204 --> 00:34:01,205
- What?
- A clip-on.

760
00:34:01,289 --> 00:34:03,499
What is this?

761
00:34:03,583 --> 00:34:05,835
- This is for the nose. It's for your nose.
- You've got the look.

762
00:34:05,918 --> 00:34:06,961
Where did you even get these?

763
00:34:07,045 --> 00:34:08,880
I was scrolling online and went, "Oh!"

764
00:34:08,963 --> 00:34:12,133
- The moment I saw them, I thought of him.
- A lip and nose ring pack?

765
00:34:12,216 --> 00:34:14,135
- On your lip. Yeah, you clip it on.
- You put it on your lip.

766
00:34:14,218 --> 00:34:15,720
You put it on your lip? Where?

767
00:34:15,803 --> 00:34:17,096
- Yeah, like that.
- Here, like this.

768
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:18,347
Let me see.

769
00:34:18,431 --> 00:34:19,474
HE PUTS THE NOSE RING ON TOO

770
00:34:19,557 --> 00:34:21,851
Do people actually wear these, though?

771
00:34:23,144 --> 00:34:24,312
How do I look?

772
00:34:25,354 --> 00:34:27,106
ESCAPING

773
00:34:27,190 --> 00:34:28,524
Hey.

774
00:34:28,608 --> 00:34:31,194
Is this a real gift,
or are you trying to make fun of me?

775
00:34:31,277 --> 00:34:33,529
- Stop laughing so hard.
- No, it's just a little dirty here.

776
00:34:34,197 --> 00:34:36,449
Well, in any case,
they do look good on you.

777
00:34:36,532 --> 00:34:38,451
Really, they're…

778
00:34:38,534 --> 00:34:39,535
Look here.

779
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:42,872
I think you might be the only
one in showbiz who wears one of those.

780
00:34:42,955 --> 00:34:44,791
- It does boost my confidence.
- Exactly.

781
00:34:44,874 --> 00:34:46,709
It actually makes me look kind of tough.

782
00:34:46,793 --> 00:34:48,044
They don't look bad.

783
00:34:48,127 --> 00:34:50,296
- All right, let's unpack.
- Yeah.

784
00:34:50,379 --> 00:34:51,589
And make lunch.

785
00:34:52,632 --> 00:34:54,217
We need to make lunch first.

786
00:34:54,801 --> 00:34:56,177
When the guests came last time,

787
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:58,805
what threw us off was that
they asked about food right away.

788
00:34:58,888 --> 00:34:59,889
Right, right.

789
00:34:59,972 --> 00:35:01,891
- Honestly, I didn't expect that.
- Same.

790
00:35:01,974 --> 00:35:04,352
We were totally flustered,
not even sure about the menu.

791
00:35:04,435 --> 00:35:06,813
Today, we'll make
kimchi fried rice and egg soup.

792
00:35:06,896 --> 00:35:08,189
- Oh, I like that.
- That sounds good.

793
00:35:08,272 --> 00:35:09,357
Sounds perfect, right?

794
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:11,526
Woo-seok, you're the expert
when it comes to eggs.

795
00:35:11,609 --> 00:35:13,194
- I'm Mr. Egg.
- Egg soup.

796
00:35:13,277 --> 00:35:15,530
- I'll handle the eggs. Sure thing.
- Think you can do it? All right.

797
00:35:15,613 --> 00:35:17,949
Ye-eun, Kwang-soo,
we'll get on the kimchi fried rice.

798
00:35:18,032 --> 00:35:21,244
- You got it.
- What about banchan? Banchan?

799
00:35:21,327 --> 00:35:23,121
- Next…
- Banchan.

800
00:35:23,204 --> 00:35:26,290
Exactly. We need to prepare
some basic banchan.

801
00:35:26,374 --> 00:35:28,334
Did Kwang-soo bring all this banchan?

802
00:35:28,417 --> 00:35:30,211
- I brought them.
- Wow, Woo-seok.

803
00:35:30,294 --> 00:35:31,671
I love stir-fried squid.

804
00:35:31,754 --> 00:35:34,006
- What's that? Oh, sausages?
- Vienna sausages.

805
00:35:34,090 --> 00:35:35,967
Did you buy all the fish cakes in town?

806
00:35:36,050 --> 00:35:37,051
There's a ton.

807
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:39,637
- Good work. Nice.
- We've got a toaster. And kimchi.

808
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:42,140
I brought bread
and some peanut butter too.

809
00:35:42,223 --> 00:35:43,850
We are fully stocked.

810
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:45,726
Now, this feels like a fridge at home.

811
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:47,228
- Banchan everywhere.
- It feels reassuring.

812
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:49,730
Hey, should we put some buns in here?

813
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:51,023
Look at that.

814
00:35:51,774 --> 00:35:53,943
- I like the ones with veggies.
- Yeah, I like the veggie too.

815
00:35:54,026 --> 00:35:56,028
Let's put the pizza ones on the top shelf.

816
00:35:56,112 --> 00:35:58,197
Mmm. Smells good.

817
00:35:58,281 --> 00:35:59,949
I think they're gonna love these.

818
00:36:00,032 --> 00:36:01,409
They'll definitely love them.

819
00:36:01,492 --> 00:36:02,535
Steamed buns.

820
00:36:02,618 --> 00:36:04,620
CHECKLIST 1. ORGANIZE BANCHAN
2. PUT BUNS IN THE WARMER

821
00:36:05,204 --> 00:36:07,123
MEANWHILE, WOO-SEOK
CAREFULLY WASHES SOME RICE

822
00:36:07,707 --> 00:36:10,084
AND COOKS IT LIKE A PRO

823
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:12,753
3. COOK RICE
4. ROAST SWEET POTATOES

824
00:36:13,838 --> 00:36:15,006
Sweet potatoes?

825
00:36:16,132 --> 00:36:18,259
- You started the rice?
- Yeah, I started it.

826
00:36:18,342 --> 00:36:20,219
We need to prep the rest of it.

827
00:36:20,303 --> 00:36:23,306
- We just need the ham for the fried rice.
- We do have some Spam in there.

828
00:36:23,389 --> 00:36:25,266
- Yeah.
- Do we also have tuna?

829
00:36:25,349 --> 00:36:27,351
- You don't need both of them.
- Why not?

830
00:36:27,435 --> 00:36:29,770
You don't add Spam and tuna.

831
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:32,398
But I really like
kimchi fried rice with tuna.

832
00:36:32,481 --> 00:36:34,901
You have to choose one or the other.

833
00:36:34,984 --> 00:36:36,527
I prefer Spam.

834
00:36:36,611 --> 00:36:39,363
- Actually, I'm a Spam person too.
- I like Spam better too.

835
00:36:39,447 --> 00:36:41,282
Then why don't we do the tuna separately?

836
00:36:41,365 --> 00:36:43,618
- You want to make two different dishes?
- Yeah.

837
00:36:43,701 --> 00:36:45,661
- Hang on.
- Or maybe we just put it in the rice.

838
00:36:45,745 --> 00:36:47,747
- Let's just forget the tuna.
- We can just forget the tuna.

839
00:36:47,830 --> 00:36:49,540
Eight with ham, two with tuna.

840
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:51,667
- Are you kidding?
- Are you serious right now?

841
00:36:51,751 --> 00:36:53,336
Why would you go to all that trouble?

842
00:36:53,419 --> 00:36:55,087
Is there a rule that says
we have to use tuna?

843
00:36:55,171 --> 00:36:56,505
I think you're the only one who wants it.

844
00:36:56,589 --> 00:36:59,133
- Two with tuna, eight with ham.
- No, people wouldn't miss it.

845
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,801
Fine, I'll just eat it myself, then.

846
00:37:00,885 --> 00:37:03,429
You can literally eat it
right when you get back home.

847
00:37:03,512 --> 00:37:04,764
I'll eat it, okay?

848
00:37:04,847 --> 00:37:05,973
I want to eat it. Geez.

849
00:37:06,057 --> 00:37:08,601
Do you have
some kind of history with tuna?

850
00:37:08,684 --> 00:37:10,311
What kind of history could he have?

851
00:37:10,394 --> 00:37:13,231
Roasting me in that calm, quiet voice.

852
00:37:13,314 --> 00:37:15,316
He's being so gentle about it.

853
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:18,069
All right, fine.
Go with Spam if that makes you happy.

854
00:37:19,779 --> 00:37:22,198
- All right, I think this will do.
- We're all done.

855
00:37:22,281 --> 00:37:23,324
I hope they're good.

856
00:37:23,950 --> 00:37:26,285
HE SHAKES OFF THE WATER

857
00:37:29,622 --> 00:37:31,207
- Get the big ones, Kwang-soo.
- Okay.

858
00:37:31,707 --> 00:37:32,708
I think that's good.

859
00:37:35,628 --> 00:37:37,213
CURRENT TIME
10:30 A.M.

860
00:37:37,296 --> 00:37:38,923
We've got everything ready, right?

861
00:37:39,006 --> 00:37:41,008
The guests will be here around 11:00.

862
00:37:41,092 --> 00:37:43,261
We only have 30 minutes left.

863
00:37:43,344 --> 00:37:45,304
When they get here,
we'll start with the orientation.

864
00:37:45,388 --> 00:37:48,015
- Got it.
- And then we'll give them a tour.

865
00:37:48,099 --> 00:37:49,684
- After that--
- Then we'll start cooking, right?

866
00:37:49,767 --> 00:37:52,061
We'll make lunch for everyone
while they unpack.

867
00:37:52,144 --> 00:37:53,396
- We're on it.
- Kimchi fried rice.

868
00:37:53,479 --> 00:37:54,981
- That won't take too long.
- Yeah.

869
00:37:55,064 --> 00:37:57,108
Compared to last time,
we're more… We're not panicking.

870
00:37:57,191 --> 00:37:58,526
We're relaxed for sure.

871
00:37:58,609 --> 00:38:00,778
- We're not panicking. We know what to do.
- I know.

872
00:38:00,861 --> 00:38:02,863
Last time, we didn't have
a second to stand around.

873
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:05,408
- We had no time.
- We didn't have any time to do this.

874
00:38:05,491 --> 00:38:06,701
1 HOUR LATER

875
00:38:06,784 --> 00:38:08,369
Hyung, things are getting hectic.

876
00:38:08,452 --> 00:38:09,745
- Wait, wait.
- What do we do?

877
00:38:09,829 --> 00:38:12,498
For crying out loud.
We were relaxed earlier. What happened?

878
00:38:12,581 --> 00:38:14,125
I forgot minced garlic. Minced garlic!

879
00:38:14,208 --> 00:38:15,418
Hey, where's the soy sauce?

880
00:38:15,501 --> 00:38:18,212
No, no, too salty, too salty. Stop! Stop!

881
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:21,090
Be careful what you say,
before it all turns into hell.

882
00:38:21,173 --> 00:38:22,883
WHAT KIND OF FUTURE AWAITS THEM?

883
00:38:23,843 --> 00:38:27,513
- I'd say, well… Oh, hang on.
- Oh!

884
00:38:27,596 --> 00:38:28,931
You've got a call?

885
00:38:29,015 --> 00:38:31,058
- Hold on. Nobody panic.
- Oh.

886
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:33,477
We're getting calls already?
It's not time yet.

887
00:38:35,396 --> 00:38:37,148
- Who is it?
- Hello?

888
00:38:37,982 --> 00:38:39,734
<i>Oh, hello, sir!</i>

889
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:41,444
Yeah, hi. Who is this?

890
00:38:41,527 --> 00:38:43,237
This is like last time.

891
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:45,531
<i>We have a reservation under Kim Min-ju.</i>

892
00:38:45,614 --> 00:38:46,699
How many people?

893
00:38:46,782 --> 00:38:48,117
We're four people.

894
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:49,910
FOUR PEOPLE

895
00:38:49,994 --> 00:38:50,995
I like her energy.

896
00:38:51,078 --> 00:38:52,872
<i>We just got here</i>
<i>and didn't know where to go.</i>

897
00:38:52,955 --> 00:38:54,790
Okay, then you can just come on up.

898
00:38:54,874 --> 00:38:55,958
<i>We'll see you soon.</i>

899
00:38:56,042 --> 00:38:57,209
First is Min-ju.

900
00:38:57,752 --> 00:39:00,671
Just… Oh, hang on.

901
00:39:00,755 --> 00:39:03,674
- Man, here we go. It's happening again.
- What is it?

902
00:39:03,758 --> 00:39:06,552
Hey, do we have a foreigner?
His name's Bryan.

903
00:39:06,635 --> 00:39:08,637
- Bryan?
- Fly to the Sky.

904
00:39:08,721 --> 00:39:10,389
You think so?

905
00:39:10,473 --> 00:39:11,766
"That makes me Hwanhee."

906
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:16,020
Oh, a text from Busan?

907
00:39:16,103 --> 00:39:17,355
- Busan?
- He's asking about lunch.

908
00:39:17,438 --> 00:39:18,522
I WAS WONDERING
WHEN WE'LL HAVE LUNCH

909
00:39:18,606 --> 00:39:19,607
You see that?

910
00:39:19,690 --> 00:39:21,233
Let's not announce the time just yet.

911
00:39:21,317 --> 00:39:23,194
- Tell them it's a secret.
- "Once you unpack."

912
00:39:23,277 --> 00:39:24,445
"Once you unpack."

913
00:39:24,528 --> 00:39:28,407
"Lunch will be provided once you unpack."

914
00:39:28,491 --> 00:39:31,077
- "Provided." Nice. Very professional.
- It is, isn't it?

915
00:39:31,744 --> 00:39:33,371
Nam-soon and Jo Nam…

916
00:39:33,454 --> 00:39:35,664
Nam-soon and Nam-jin?
Are they brother and sister?

917
00:39:35,748 --> 00:39:37,375
- They must be.
- I guess so.

918
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:38,834
"Are you siblings?"

919
00:39:41,128 --> 00:39:43,047
Hmm?

920
00:39:43,130 --> 00:39:45,216
I'm going to say, "We're brothers."

921
00:39:46,300 --> 00:39:48,844
BROTHERS?

922
00:39:48,928 --> 00:39:51,514
If we were brother and sister,
you'd be the girl.

923
00:39:51,597 --> 00:39:52,723
WE'VE GOT TWO BROTHERS
WHO SEEM CLOSE

924
00:39:53,307 --> 00:39:56,268
OVER MOUNTAINS
AND ACROSS WATER

925
00:39:56,352 --> 00:39:59,105
- Do you see that? Wow.
- See what? Oh!

926
00:39:59,188 --> 00:40:01,857
"Jae-seok's B&B Rules."

927
00:40:01,941 --> 00:40:03,067
It says we can play and talk nonstop.

928
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:04,944
FROM HERE, YOU CAN TALK NONSTOP,
PLAY HARD AND MESS AROUND

929
00:40:05,027 --> 00:40:07,363
- That's our specialty.
- That's true.

930
00:40:07,446 --> 00:40:09,365
But still, if we goof around too much…

931
00:40:09,990 --> 00:40:11,367
We're here.

932
00:40:11,992 --> 00:40:13,994
- Hello.
- Hello.

933
00:40:15,329 --> 00:40:16,330
Mom.

934
00:40:16,414 --> 00:40:17,623
ANOTHER FAMILY OF GUESTS?

935
00:40:17,706 --> 00:40:18,707
- You're late.
- This is silly.

936
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:21,627
- Have a good time. Bye.
- Mom, I'm gonna miss you.

937
00:40:22,211 --> 00:40:23,504
A SOLO GUEST
DROPPED OFF BY HER MOM

938
00:40:23,587 --> 00:40:26,632
- Hello. Hello.
- She's beautiful.

939
00:40:26,715 --> 00:40:28,926
- Is she a celebrity?
- Right? She's pretty.

940
00:40:29,593 --> 00:40:31,137
Oh, there are a lot of people.

941
00:40:31,220 --> 00:40:32,346
NO SHARING INFO BEYOND NAMES

942
00:40:32,930 --> 00:40:35,015
- Hello, everyone.
- Hello.

943
00:40:35,599 --> 00:40:36,725
Where are you from?

944
00:40:36,809 --> 00:40:39,270
- I'm from Siheung. Yeah.
- Siheung?

945
00:40:39,353 --> 00:40:42,064
THEY CAN SAY WHERE THEY LIVE

946
00:40:42,148 --> 00:40:43,941
- Hello.
- Hello.

947
00:40:44,024 --> 00:40:45,568
- Hello.
- Hello.

948
00:40:45,651 --> 00:40:47,903
- He looks like a rocker.
- Hello.

949
00:40:47,987 --> 00:40:51,115
IS HE REALLY A MUSICIAN?

950
00:40:51,699 --> 00:40:53,951
- They brought kids?
- Yeah, kids.

951
00:40:54,034 --> 00:40:56,287
- It's a dad and his daughters.
- Yeah, they're with their dad.

952
00:40:56,370 --> 00:40:58,914
- Take the sleeping bag.
- Does everyone know what they're carrying?

953
00:40:58,998 --> 00:41:00,458
- Hello.
- Hello.

954
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:01,542
FATHER AND HIS DAUGHTERS,
CORRECT

955
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:03,127
- Isn't that heavy?
- It's okay.

956
00:41:03,210 --> 00:41:04,336
A TOUGH-LOOKING DAD
AND HIS DAUGHTERS

957
00:41:04,420 --> 00:41:07,798
They'll be here around 11:00.
I wonder how many people are coming.

958
00:41:07,882 --> 00:41:10,843
We don't know anything about the second
group of guests. I'm so curious.

959
00:41:11,635 --> 00:41:14,221
TO SATISFY YOUR CURIOSITY

960
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:16,765
- Can you carry that by yourself?
- Oh, I'm all right.

961
00:41:17,808 --> 00:41:20,060
We're almost there. This is awesome.

962
00:41:20,144 --> 00:41:21,228
"Jae-seok's B&B."

963
