1200
00:50:17,431 --> 00:50:18,640
- We'll make the soup.
- Okay.

1201
00:50:18,724 --> 00:50:21,101
Then Ye-eun and I will make the rice.

1202
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:23,937
By the way,
Group Two definitely seems more…

1203
00:50:24,021 --> 00:50:25,480
- Yeah?
- They're calmer.

1204
00:50:25,564 --> 00:50:27,315
Right. They are calmer than Group One.

1205
00:50:27,399 --> 00:50:28,942
- Yeah.
- It's a little…

1206
00:50:29,026 --> 00:50:30,902
- I'm not used to it.
- Yeah, I know.

1207
00:50:30,986 --> 00:50:32,696
- I mean…
- They're pretty chill.

1208
00:50:32,779 --> 00:50:35,323
Not with me! That's my promise to you!

1209
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:37,784
THE 1ST GROUP OF GUESTS
WAS FULL OF ENERGY

1210
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:41,371
- Lee Kwang-soo!
- Lee Kwang-soo!

1211
00:50:41,455 --> 00:50:42,956
GROUP 2 IN THE SAME SITUATION

1212
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:44,416
You can take this as an absolute promise!

1213
00:50:44,499 --> 00:50:45,709
Wow.

1214
00:50:45,792 --> 00:50:47,294
CHILL

1215
00:50:48,086 --> 00:50:50,255
We've got three days and two nights.

1216
00:50:50,338 --> 00:50:51,757
We have time to warm them up.

1217
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:54,134
- First impressions are important.
- Right.

1218
00:50:54,217 --> 00:50:56,344
We need to have this ready right on time.

1219
00:50:56,428 --> 00:50:58,096
Like it's no big deal.

1220
00:50:58,180 --> 00:51:00,223
- Like we've been doing this forever.
- Exactly.

1221
00:51:00,307 --> 00:51:03,727
- Drinking water. Should we use that?
- Sure. Yeah.

1222
00:51:03,810 --> 00:51:05,645
- We can take that and stick it in here.
- Okay.

1223
00:51:05,729 --> 00:51:08,106
That's 19 liters,
but it's been used a bit,

1224
00:51:08,190 --> 00:51:10,442
so I think there's about 16 liters left.

1225
00:51:10,525 --> 00:51:11,902
None of us know what that means.

1226
00:51:11,985 --> 00:51:13,612
- Right.
- We just have to eyeball it.

1227
00:51:13,695 --> 00:51:15,822
If you move that, the water will
come pouring out.

1228
00:51:15,906 --> 00:51:17,532
Quick. We have to be quick.

1229
00:51:17,616 --> 00:51:19,034
One, two, three.

1230
00:51:20,285 --> 00:51:21,703
PLUGGING THE OPENING
SO THE WATER DOESN'T SPILL

1231
00:51:22,913 --> 00:51:23,914
Gosh.

1232
00:51:25,540 --> 00:51:27,959
- Don't we have to use it all?
- I think so.

1233
00:51:28,668 --> 00:51:29,753
RECIPE BOOK
EGG SOUP INGREDIENTS

1234
00:51:29,836 --> 00:51:31,213
4 EGGS, 1L OF WATER,
1/3 LARGE GREEN ONION

1235
00:51:31,296 --> 00:51:32,589
20 SERVINGS = 5 L

1236
00:51:32,672 --> 00:51:35,008
THEY'RE POURING IN 16L RIGHT NOW

1237
00:51:35,592 --> 00:51:37,552
THAT MAKES 60 SERVINGS TOTAL

1238
00:51:37,636 --> 00:51:39,679
- Oh, no.
- This is perfect.

1239
00:51:40,972 --> 00:51:46,603
KEEPS POURING IN WATER

1240
00:51:47,687 --> 00:51:48,730
Oh, it's out.

1241
00:51:50,357 --> 00:51:54,694
SHAKING OUT EVERY LAST DROP

1242
00:51:54,778 --> 00:51:57,114
- Is that enough water?
- It should be.

1243
00:51:57,781 --> 00:51:59,616
You know how to
make kimchi fried rice, right?

1244
00:51:59,699 --> 00:52:00,951
I've never made it, but…

1245
00:52:01,034 --> 00:52:02,536
- You've never made it?
- No.

1246
00:52:02,619 --> 00:52:04,538
- Now I'm worried.
- No, trust me.

1247
00:52:04,621 --> 00:52:05,997
I can get it done in no time.

1248
00:52:06,081 --> 00:52:07,124
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

1249
00:52:07,749 --> 00:52:09,626
Seriously, I'm not kidding. I've got this.

1250
00:52:09,709 --> 00:52:12,295
With some scallion oil and garlic.

1251
00:52:12,379 --> 00:52:14,673
Are you supposed to put scallions
in kimchi fried rice?

1252
00:52:15,757 --> 00:52:16,842
SIDE-EYE

1253
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:19,511
A LOOK OF DOUBT

1254
00:52:19,594 --> 00:52:21,138
You don't put scallions in it.

1255
00:52:22,305 --> 00:52:24,975
I was going to make scallion oil
with some garlic…

1256
00:52:25,058 --> 00:52:26,977
You've never made it before, have you?

1257
00:52:27,060 --> 00:52:28,186
Actually, I have.

1258
00:52:29,646 --> 00:52:32,440
You don't put garlic and scallions in.

1259
00:52:33,275 --> 00:52:36,236
No, you make scallion oil
with some garlic and then--

1260
00:52:36,319 --> 00:52:38,071
No. First you stir-fry the kimchi.

1261
00:52:38,155 --> 00:52:39,239
BOTH DIGGING IN THEIR HEELS

1262
00:52:39,322 --> 00:52:40,866
- No.
- Hold on a second.

1263
00:52:41,449 --> 00:52:42,617
- Look--
- I know I'm right.

1264
00:52:42,701 --> 00:52:44,661
No, look, seriously.

1265
00:52:44,744 --> 00:52:45,871
Unbelievable.

1266
00:52:45,954 --> 00:52:47,455
FACT CHECK
HOW TO MAKE KIMCHI FRIED RICE

1267
00:52:47,539 --> 00:52:49,040
You put scallions in it?

1268
00:52:49,124 --> 00:52:51,251
<i>Let's take a look at</i>
<i>how to make kimchi fried rice.</i>

1269
00:52:51,334 --> 00:52:53,503
<i>It tastes even better</i>
<i>with some green onion.</i>

1270
00:52:54,629 --> 00:52:56,089
See?

1271
00:52:56,173 --> 00:52:58,466
<i>Add two spoons of cooking oil.</i>

1272
00:52:58,550 --> 00:53:00,719
<i>Make some scallion oil first.</i>

1273
00:53:01,928 --> 00:53:04,389
I've never had scallions
in my kimchi fried rice.

1274
00:53:04,472 --> 00:53:05,974
- See, Ye-eun?
- Yeah.

1275
00:53:06,808 --> 00:53:09,019
- Don't get smart with me.
- Okay.

1276
00:53:09,102 --> 00:53:10,896
You know we're frying eggs too, right?

1277
00:53:10,979 --> 00:53:12,647
Woo-seok is going to do that.

1278
00:53:13,231 --> 00:53:14,232
Woo-seok will fry the eggs…

1279
00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:15,317
THE EGG GUY AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

1280
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:17,694
- I'll handle the eggs. Of course.
- Do you have what it takes?

1281
00:53:17,777 --> 00:53:19,279
STARTING ON THE FRIED EGGS
FOR THE FRIED RICE!

1282
00:53:19,905 --> 00:53:21,865
JAE-SEOK PREPS SCALLION OIL TOO

1283
00:53:21,948 --> 00:53:23,909
We're one team now,
so let's stick together.

1284
00:53:23,992 --> 00:53:25,076
Sounds good.

1285
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:27,412
FILLING OUT
THE REGISTRATION FORM

1286
00:53:28,038 --> 00:53:29,289
REASON FOR APPLYING:
I WAS GETTING TIRED

1287
00:53:29,372 --> 00:53:30,498
OF MY REPETITIVE ROUTINE

1288
00:53:30,582 --> 00:53:33,460
TO MAKE MEMORIES WITH MY DAD
AND MY LITTLE SISTER!

1289
00:53:33,543 --> 00:53:35,295
What did you write for why you applied?

1290
00:53:35,378 --> 00:53:37,672
"To make memories
with my dad and my sister."

1291
00:53:38,506 --> 00:53:41,509
TO MAKE GOOD MEMORIES
WITH MY FAMILY

1292
00:53:42,093 --> 00:53:43,261
TO MAKE MEMORIES
BEFORE ENLISTING

1293
00:53:43,345 --> 00:53:45,096
GUESTS GATHERED HERE
FOR THEIR OWN REASONS

1294
00:53:45,180 --> 00:53:46,514
"Food I want to eat"?

1295
00:53:46,598 --> 00:53:48,642
FOOD YOU WANT TO EAT

1296
00:53:48,725 --> 00:53:49,768
Okay.

1297
00:53:51,061 --> 00:53:53,355
ANYTHING MADE BY
MR. BYEON WOO-SEOK

1298
00:53:53,438 --> 00:53:54,898
What are your concerns?

1299
00:53:55,482 --> 00:53:56,524
I snore.

1300
00:53:56,608 --> 00:53:59,486
Should I write, "Holding in my farts"?

1301
00:53:59,569 --> 00:54:00,904
- No, I can't.
- Bodily functions.

1302
00:54:00,987 --> 00:54:02,572
Byeon Woo-seok is here.

1303
00:54:02,656 --> 00:54:04,532
- Want to get some buns?
- Okay.

1304
00:54:05,408 --> 00:54:07,285
- I'm hungry. I can't wait.
- Me too. I'm starving.

1305
00:54:07,369 --> 00:54:08,495
CURRENT TIME
12:08 P.M.

1306
00:54:08,578 --> 00:54:11,164
- They're cooking now.
- Oh, he's so handsome.

1307
00:54:11,248 --> 00:54:13,625
- He is.
- Let's not bother him. He's cooking.

1308
00:54:14,376 --> 00:54:17,796
HARD TO INTERRUPT
WHEN HE LOOKS LIKE THAT

1309
00:54:17,879 --> 00:54:19,798
Oh, Hye-jeong is here.

1310
00:54:20,340 --> 00:54:22,676
- Ha-na.
- We're just really hungry.

1311
00:54:22,759 --> 00:54:24,552
Just a little bit longer.
We'll be done soon.

1312
00:54:24,636 --> 00:54:25,971
- Hey, Hye-jeong.
- Yes?

1313
00:54:26,054 --> 00:54:27,389
What are you doing here?

1314
00:54:27,472 --> 00:54:30,558
- I couldn't help but notice the artwork.
- Oh, you mean…

1315
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:38,066
TITLE: MAN CRACKING EGGS

1316
00:54:38,149 --> 00:54:39,526
You're not worried about us, are you?

1317
00:54:39,609 --> 00:54:41,611
- Nah, looks like you're doing great.
- Yeah, yeah. Of course.

1318
00:54:41,695 --> 00:54:43,863
TALKING TO JAE-SEOK
BUT LOOKING AT WOO-SEOK

1319
00:54:43,947 --> 00:54:44,990
- Hye-jeong.
- Yes?

1320
00:54:45,073 --> 00:54:46,866
- Don't worry. We got this.
- Okay.

1321
00:54:47,742 --> 00:54:50,245
- Please make it delicious.
- Come on.

1322
00:54:50,328 --> 00:54:52,038
Don't you worry about a thing.

1323
00:54:52,122 --> 00:54:55,417
- We could do this with our eyes closed.
- Yeah, seriously. That's right.

1324
00:54:55,500 --> 00:54:57,836
Already eating? Is that <i>jjondeugi</i>?

1325
00:54:57,919 --> 00:54:59,212
It looks so yummy.

1326
00:54:59,296 --> 00:55:01,214
I smell roasted sweet potatoes.

1327
00:55:01,298 --> 00:55:02,841
I'm hungry.

1328
00:55:02,924 --> 00:55:05,927
- I'm wondering if you're all athletes.
- I'm not.

1329
00:55:06,011 --> 00:55:09,264
- It feels like you're athletes.
- I've never played sports in my life.

1330
00:55:09,347 --> 00:55:11,016
- I'm so curious.
- I know.

1331
00:55:11,099 --> 00:55:12,350
Have you done your service?

1332
00:55:12,434 --> 00:55:14,811
- Give it time. I'll fill you in.
- He'll fill us in later.

1333
00:55:14,894 --> 00:55:16,104
I guess you haven't…

1334
00:55:16,187 --> 00:55:19,691
- You haven't done it, have you?
- Well, maybe I have, maybe I haven't.

1335
00:55:19,774 --> 00:55:20,775
Oh, I haven't done mine yet.

1336
00:55:20,859 --> 00:55:22,485
You're in the military
right now, aren't you?

1337
00:55:22,569 --> 00:55:23,737
Oh, all right, I'll stop.

1338
00:55:23,820 --> 00:55:24,904
A KNOWING LOOK

1339
00:55:24,988 --> 00:55:28,074
Oh, man, I really want to know
what people do for work.

1340
00:55:28,158 --> 00:55:29,367
I'm just so curious.

1341
00:55:29,951 --> 00:55:31,077
- Ye-eun.
- Yeah?

1342
00:55:31,161 --> 00:55:33,997
- You need to take the lead on this.
- Okay. Seriously, I've got this.

1343
00:55:34,622 --> 00:55:36,416
- Olive, it's healthier.
- Mm-hmm.

1344
00:55:37,125 --> 00:55:38,126
A GENEROUS POUR

1345
00:55:38,209 --> 00:55:40,086
- Okay, enough. That's enough.
- No, I think it needs more.

1346
00:55:40,170 --> 00:55:41,338
Don't put in too much.

1347
00:55:41,421 --> 00:55:42,797
- I'll add some sweetener.
- Oh, okay.

1348
00:55:42,881 --> 00:55:45,383
ADDING SWEETNESS

1349
00:55:45,467 --> 00:55:46,509
It should be a little sweet.

1350
00:55:46,593 --> 00:55:48,636
- Too sweet! Too sweet!
- A little sweet is better.

1351
00:55:48,720 --> 00:55:51,097
- No, no, it can't be too sweet.
- No?

1352
00:55:51,181 --> 00:55:53,516
- Hold on, check the recipe again.
- No, I know.

1353
00:55:53,600 --> 00:55:55,143
- Now what?
- Some chili powder.

1354
00:55:56,519 --> 00:55:59,189
- Too spicy!
- No, it's… No, no.

1355
00:55:59,272 --> 00:56:00,732
Soy sauce, then.

1356
00:56:00,815 --> 00:56:02,192
- Soy is a must.
- Just a little.

1357
00:56:02,275 --> 00:56:03,568
- Don't add too much.
- Just a bit.

1358
00:56:03,651 --> 00:56:04,861
I think that's enough. Really.

1359
00:56:04,944 --> 00:56:07,030
- Maybe a little more.
- No, too salty!

1360
00:56:07,113 --> 00:56:09,282
IGNORING

1361
00:56:09,366 --> 00:56:11,826
- Stop! Stop!
- No, it's-- But…

1362
00:56:11,910 --> 00:56:14,579
Stop! Stop! Stop!

1363
00:56:14,662 --> 00:56:16,289
Are they all right in there?

1364
00:56:17,332 --> 00:56:18,917
Now I'm worried.

1365
00:56:19,501 --> 00:56:22,212
Aw, you know, my right arm
feels like it's about to fall off.

1366
00:56:22,796 --> 00:56:23,922
SUPER GOOEY

1367
00:56:24,005 --> 00:56:25,924
See, I told you,
you put in too much syrup.

1368
00:56:26,007 --> 00:56:27,592
It'll be fine when we add the rice.

1369
00:56:27,675 --> 00:56:28,968
I have a bad feeling.

1370
00:56:29,052 --> 00:56:31,304
- Oh, the Spam.
- Hey, we forgot the Spam.

1371
00:56:31,388 --> 00:56:34,974
- Hurry. Chop up some Spam.
- Once we add this…

1372
00:56:35,058 --> 00:56:36,226
should we add more sugar?

1373
00:56:36,309 --> 00:56:37,310
No.

1374
00:56:37,394 --> 00:56:39,062
GLARE

1375
00:56:39,145 --> 00:56:40,814
- More soy sauce?
- No. Definitely not.

1376
00:56:40,897 --> 00:56:42,190
How about <i>dashida</i>?

1377
00:56:42,273 --> 00:56:45,568
You said you were confident.
Why do you keep adding things?

1378
00:56:45,652 --> 00:56:48,238
- Yeah.
- We have less time than I thought.

1379
00:56:48,822 --> 00:56:49,864
Hold on.

1380
00:56:50,824 --> 00:56:52,700
40 MINUTES UNTIL SERVING

1381
00:56:52,784 --> 00:56:54,369
Why isn't this working?
Do you have any idea?

1382
00:56:54,452 --> 00:56:55,453
It's not working?

1383
00:56:55,537 --> 00:56:56,704
THINGS ARE NOT
WORKING OUT HERE EITHER

1384
00:56:56,788 --> 00:56:57,914
- Oh, this is bad.
- What's that?

1385
00:56:57,997 --> 00:56:59,749
Are these the eggs for <i>gyeran-mari</i>?

1386
00:56:59,833 --> 00:57:02,293
- Are there eggs just for <i>gyeran-mari</i>?
- No, but--

1387
00:57:02,377 --> 00:57:04,254
COOKING SKILLS ATROPHIED

1388
00:57:04,337 --> 00:57:05,338
What else could it be?

1389
00:57:05,422 --> 00:57:06,881
EVEN WOO-SEOK, THE ONE
THEY WERE COUNTING ON, FUMBLES

1390
00:57:06,965 --> 00:57:09,801
All right, let's get it together.
Where's the ham?

1391
00:57:09,884 --> 00:57:12,137
I mean, I haven't cooked
in bulk before either.

1392
00:57:12,220 --> 00:57:14,013
I can't get the portions right.

1393
00:57:14,097 --> 00:57:16,015
It's turning into kimchi porridge.

1394
00:57:16,099 --> 00:57:17,100
STILL GOOEY

1395
00:57:17,183 --> 00:57:18,977
Hyung, should we just order something?

1396
00:57:19,060 --> 00:57:21,229
- No way.
- How about a kimchi rice bowl instead?

1397
00:57:21,312 --> 00:57:23,356
How about some <i>gochujang </i>stew?

1398
00:57:24,065 --> 00:57:28,361
We cooked better than we expected
last time, and I think we got a little…

1399
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:29,946
Complacent.

1400
00:57:30,029 --> 00:57:31,072
Uh-oh.

1401
00:57:32,115 --> 00:57:33,992
Should I put the rice in now?

1402
00:57:34,075 --> 00:57:35,660
I think it'll get mushy.

1403
00:57:36,327 --> 00:57:38,079
Hyung, you've got to put the rice in now.
You've got to.

1404
00:57:38,163 --> 00:57:39,789
No, no, then it won't be fried rice.

1405
00:57:39,873 --> 00:57:41,374
- Wait a second.
- It won't be fried rice.

1406
00:57:41,458 --> 00:57:42,500
Well then, what is this?

1407
00:57:42,584 --> 00:57:45,253
What is it? What exactly did we make?

1408
00:57:45,336 --> 00:57:46,880
- I mean, it's…
- You said you were confident.

1409
00:57:46,963 --> 00:57:48,506
You said you were confident.

1410
00:57:48,590 --> 00:57:50,467
I've never made it in bulk.

1411
00:57:50,550 --> 00:57:53,219
We're supposed to use cold rice for this.
Is it too sticky?

1412
00:57:53,303 --> 00:57:55,013
- It's fine. It'll work.
- Is it okay?

1413
00:57:57,474 --> 00:57:58,600
THEY PUT IN THE RICE,
THEIR LAST HOPE

1414
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:01,644
We need more rice. I'll go get it.

1415
00:58:01,728 --> 00:58:03,646
My right arm is gonna fall off. Shit.

1416
00:58:03,730 --> 00:58:04,731
SWITCHING TO BOTH HANDS

1417
00:58:04,814 --> 00:58:05,815
Ugh, shoot.

1418
00:58:05,899 --> 00:58:07,859
We shouldn't have picked
kimchi fried rice.

1419
00:58:08,443 --> 00:58:09,444
Oh, shit.

1420
00:58:09,527 --> 00:58:11,446
VEINS POPPING OUT
OF HIS FOREARM

1421
00:58:12,447 --> 00:58:13,698
Oh, I really--

1422
00:58:13,781 --> 00:58:15,867
I feel like I'm inside
the kimchi fried rice right now.

1423
00:58:15,950 --> 00:58:17,368
Oh, shit.

1424
00:58:17,452 --> 00:58:19,329
Ye-eun, can you honestly say
you made this rice?

1425
00:58:19,412 --> 00:58:20,872
- Yes.
- I'm doing all the work.

1426
00:58:20,955 --> 00:58:23,082
I seasoned it 'cause you wouldn't.

1427
00:58:23,166 --> 00:58:24,334
Hey, shut your mouth.

1428
00:58:24,417 --> 00:58:26,586
- Captain.
- Oh, hey!

1429
00:58:26,669 --> 00:58:27,712
- Captain.
- Oh, hey!

1430
00:58:27,795 --> 00:58:28,922
ONE OF THE GUESTS
SUDDENLY COMES OVER

1431
00:58:29,005 --> 00:58:30,882
I was wondering, do we have iced coffee?

1432
00:58:30,965 --> 00:58:33,009
We're gonna pick up some coffee later.

1433
00:58:33,092 --> 00:58:34,302
With cups of ice.

1434
00:58:34,385 --> 00:58:36,137
It'll be here soon. Just hang on a bit.

1435
00:58:36,221 --> 00:58:38,973
We already ordered it,
so don't worry. It'll be here soon.

1436
00:58:39,057 --> 00:58:41,142
We had a feeling you'd ask for it
right about now.

1437
00:58:41,226 --> 00:58:42,936
- Hold on. Ye-eun.
- Should I taste it?

1438
00:58:43,019 --> 00:58:44,270
Give it a taste.

1439
00:58:44,854 --> 00:58:46,564
IT'S FINALLY TIME TO TASTE IT

1440
00:58:46,648 --> 00:58:49,526
- Mmm. It's good.
- It's okay?

1441
00:58:49,609 --> 00:58:50,985
Hey, come taste it.

1442
00:58:51,069 --> 00:58:52,362
- Hey, guys.
- Yeah, tasty.

1443
00:58:52,445 --> 00:58:53,821
- Yes?
- Come on. Give it a taste.

1444
00:58:53,905 --> 00:58:54,906
Yeah, sure.

1445
00:58:54,989 --> 00:58:58,451
COMPLETELY BURNED OUT

1446
00:58:58,535 --> 00:59:00,078
- Really, it's good.
- Damn.

1447
00:59:00,161 --> 00:59:01,871
- Seriously, it's good. I mean it.
- Damn.

1448
00:59:01,955 --> 00:59:04,290
WHAT WILL WOO-SEOK SAY?

1449
00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:07,961
NERVOUS

1450
00:59:10,296 --> 00:59:11,297
How is it?

1451
00:59:13,216 --> 00:59:15,009
SHAKES HEAD

1452
00:59:16,302 --> 00:59:17,345
What's missing?

1453
00:59:18,012 --> 00:59:20,348
I don't know, but it's definitely salty.

1454
00:59:20,431 --> 00:59:22,058
What do you think we should add?

1455
00:59:23,226 --> 00:59:25,687
- Oh, kimchi juice.
- Right, kimchi juice.

1456
00:59:25,770 --> 00:59:28,022
RUSHING

1457
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:31,776
Hey, hey, wait. Not so much.
Not so much. That's enough.

1458
00:59:31,859 --> 00:59:33,778
- Should we add a little more soy sauce?
- Oh, soy sauce.

1459
00:59:33,861 --> 00:59:35,071
I'll grab it.

1460
00:59:35,154 --> 00:59:37,282
Wait, wait, let's taste it first.
Taste it first!

1461
00:59:37,865 --> 00:59:39,325
It's a bit too salty.

1462
00:59:39,409 --> 00:59:41,411
- Go get some more rice.
- Here.

1463
00:59:41,494 --> 00:59:44,038
Let's add a little more Spam and kimchi.

1464
00:59:44,122 --> 00:59:46,207
- Sesame oil. Nutty.
- Pour it around.

1465
00:59:46,291 --> 00:59:48,001
I think this is as good
as it's going to get.

1466
00:59:48,084 --> 00:59:49,085
Done.

1467
00:59:49,168 --> 00:59:51,546
- I was so confident until this morning.
- I know.

1468
00:59:51,629 --> 00:59:53,256
- It just hit us.
- I thought we'd be fine.

1469
00:59:53,339 --> 00:59:54,424
It hit us right away.

1470
00:59:55,174 --> 00:59:56,551
That kimchi fried rice just…

1471
00:59:56,634 --> 00:59:58,386
- I mean, wow.
- Seriously.

1472
00:59:58,469 --> 01:00:00,221
That rice really knocked me out.

1473
01:00:00,805 --> 01:00:02,599
THE WATER FOR 60 SERVINGS
OF SOUP CAME TO A BOIL

1474
01:00:03,099 --> 01:00:05,101
ADDING IN THE KEY INGREDIENT,
BEATEN EGGS

1475
01:00:05,184 --> 01:00:06,269
Some more salt.

1476
01:00:10,565 --> 01:00:13,860
TASTING THE SOUP

1477
01:00:16,738 --> 01:00:17,864
What the heck is this?

1478
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:21,075
This is just hot water.

1479
01:00:21,826 --> 01:00:23,036
It just tastes like nothing.

1480
01:00:23,119 --> 01:00:24,871
I don't know if I can make this work.

1481
01:00:24,954 --> 01:00:26,372
It still just tastes like hot water.

1482
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:27,707
TO THIS HE ADDS

1483
01:00:27,790 --> 01:00:28,875
RAMYEON SEASONING

1484
01:00:28,958 --> 01:00:30,168
TO THIS HE ADDS

1485
01:00:30,251 --> 01:00:31,586
YONDU

1486
01:00:32,170 --> 01:00:33,463
A SECRET INGREDIENT

1487
01:00:33,546 --> 01:00:35,381
POURING IN DASHIDA

1488
01:00:35,465 --> 01:00:37,467
LOADED WITH ALL KINDS OF MSG

1489
01:00:38,051 --> 01:00:40,053
KWANG-SOO'S EGG SOUP IS DONE

1490
01:00:40,136 --> 01:00:41,763
- Should we prep the banchan?
- Let's do it.

1491
01:00:41,846 --> 01:00:43,431
Stir-fried dried squid, fish cakes--

1492
01:00:44,015 --> 01:00:46,059
AND WOO-SEOK'S FRIED EGGS

1493
01:00:46,142 --> 01:00:47,185
Hyung, I think we're done.

1494
01:00:47,268 --> 01:00:48,519
- Oh, my goodness.
- It's done.

1495
01:00:48,603 --> 01:00:51,272
A lot of them are hungry,
so let's move it up a bit.

1496
01:00:51,356 --> 01:00:54,150
- Ten minutes early. That's always nice.
- Yeah, it's great.

1497
01:00:54,734 --> 01:00:55,943
All right, let's eat!

1498
01:00:56,027 --> 01:00:57,737
Everyone, come have lunch!

1499
01:00:57,820 --> 01:00:59,447
Time for lunch!

1500
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:01,324
- They're calling us.
- Oh, lunch is ready!

1501
01:01:01,407 --> 01:01:02,867
- Time to eat.
- I'm so hungry.

1502
01:01:02,950 --> 01:01:05,370
- Is it time for lunch?
- They're calling us in to eat.

1503
01:01:05,453 --> 01:01:08,081
Lunch was at 1:00,
but we moved it up a bit!

1504
01:01:08,164 --> 01:01:11,959
You said you were hungry,
so we picked up the pace just for you.

1505
01:01:12,043 --> 01:01:13,503
It looks delicious.

1506
01:01:13,586 --> 01:01:15,296
- Wow, look at that.
- Wow.

1507
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:17,090
Looks like they've got a couple options.

1508
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:19,008
This is your first meal,
so we decided simple was best.

1509
01:01:19,092 --> 01:01:20,093
We kept it simple.

1510
01:01:20,176 --> 01:01:23,388
Just so you know, kimchi fried rice was
what we were least confident about.

1511
01:01:23,471 --> 01:01:25,515
- We just gave it a shot.
- But we wanted to give it a shot.

1512
01:01:25,598 --> 01:01:27,475
- Enjoy, Chae-eun.
- Okay.

1513
01:01:27,558 --> 01:01:29,602
It might not be as good
as what you have at home,

1514
01:01:29,686 --> 01:01:32,897
because we basically just whipped it up,
but it should still taste good.

1515
01:01:33,481 --> 01:01:35,692
TAKING A BITE IN A HURRY

1516
01:01:35,775 --> 01:01:37,193
Mmm. It's good.

1517
01:01:37,276 --> 01:01:39,195
The kimchi fried rice
is really well-seasoned.

1518
01:01:39,278 --> 01:01:40,446
AGAINST EXPECTATIONS,
PRAISE CONTINUES

1519
01:01:40,530 --> 01:01:42,448
- How is it?
- It's good.

1520
01:01:42,532 --> 01:01:43,700
The egg soup is good.

1521
01:01:43,783 --> 01:01:45,118
- Oh!
- The egg soup's good.

1522
01:01:48,121 --> 01:01:50,707
- Yeah.
- It's great. It's delicious.

1523
01:01:50,790 --> 01:01:51,791
- You want seconds?
- Yeah.

1524
01:01:51,874 --> 01:01:53,000
Okay!

1525
01:01:53,584 --> 01:01:55,795
- Help yourself.
- I guess that means you like the soup.

1526
01:01:55,878 --> 01:01:56,879
Wow.

1527
01:01:57,547 --> 01:01:59,757
- I knew you'd want seconds. You like it?
- Oh, yeah.

1528
01:01:59,841 --> 01:02:02,552
We just threw it together. I'm glad.

1529
01:02:02,635 --> 01:02:05,346
THE GUESTS
SEEM TO ENJOY THE FOOD

1530
01:02:05,930 --> 01:02:07,640
I'm really glad they're enjoying it.

1531
01:02:08,224 --> 01:02:09,934
When you're done, this is for feedback.

1532
01:02:10,017 --> 01:02:11,477
Tell us what you think.

1533
01:02:11,561 --> 01:02:14,897
We don't care about the results at all.
We just want your feedback.

1534
01:02:14,981 --> 01:02:16,899
We won't even look at it. Really.

1535
01:02:18,067 --> 01:02:20,611
- I feel like I used all my energy again.
- Me too.

1536
01:02:21,195 --> 01:02:24,115
I just want to lie down.

1537
01:02:24,198 --> 01:02:26,868
Look, the thing is, I'm not kidding.

1538
01:02:26,951 --> 01:02:29,036
- I felt really great today.
- Oh, yeah?

1539
01:02:29,120 --> 01:02:30,538
But suddenly I feel…

1540
01:02:30,621 --> 01:02:33,750
- Unwell?
- Yeah. I think I need to be hospitalized.

1541
01:02:34,333 --> 01:02:36,919
- Hyung, would you like more soup?
- No, no, no.

1542
01:02:37,003 --> 01:02:39,756
So, after we eat,
are we gonna do something right away?

1543
01:02:39,839 --> 01:02:41,716
- Oh, we--
- Yeah.

1544
01:02:41,799 --> 01:02:44,761
We'll be doing one activity
per day with you all.

1545
01:02:44,844 --> 01:02:47,138
We'll tell you
about today's plan later, okay?

1546
01:02:47,221 --> 01:02:49,515
- Got it.
- If you want to brush your teeth, you can.

1547
01:02:49,599 --> 01:02:51,768
In the meantime,
we'll do the dishes and stuff.

1548
01:02:51,851 --> 01:02:54,312
Right, and are we allowed
to help you with those?

1549
01:02:54,395 --> 01:02:55,855
- That would be great.
- Hey, Ye-eun.

1550
01:02:55,938 --> 01:02:57,440
HER INNER THOUGHTS SLIPPED OUT

1551
01:02:57,523 --> 01:02:58,566
Come on, Ye-eun. No.

1552
01:02:58,649 --> 01:02:59,859
THE OPPAS STOP HER IN A HURRY

1553
01:02:59,942 --> 01:03:02,487
The first group helped
and we made some great memories.

1554
01:03:02,570 --> 01:03:04,947
- Careful, Ye-eun.
- Ye-eun.

1555
01:03:05,031 --> 01:03:06,449
Let us help you this time.

1556
01:03:06,532 --> 01:03:08,284
Oh, no, it's fine.

1557
01:03:08,367 --> 01:03:10,620
We don't ask our guests
to help with chores.

1558
01:03:10,703 --> 01:03:13,039
- Not at all.
- Or work with us or anything.

1559
01:03:13,122 --> 01:03:14,749
That's against our rules.

1560
01:03:14,832 --> 01:03:18,669
All right, we're gonna head out now
to pick up the coffee we ordered.

1561
01:03:18,753 --> 01:03:21,130
So should we do the dishes now,
then? We can.

1562
01:03:21,214 --> 01:03:23,674
- Oh, would you?
- Sure, let's do it.

1563
01:03:23,758 --> 01:03:26,886
- Then why don't we do it together?
- Okay, sounds good.

1564
01:03:28,179 --> 01:03:29,514
Hey, stop.

1565
01:03:29,597 --> 01:03:30,890
Chae-won.

1566
01:03:30,973 --> 01:03:33,267
- Yeah?
- Come on. Why are you doing that?

1567
01:03:33,851 --> 01:03:35,228
I told you, just leave it.

1568
01:03:36,354 --> 01:03:39,565
I-an, why are you doing this?

1569
01:03:39,649 --> 01:03:41,484
Ha-na, stop.

1570
01:03:42,068 --> 01:03:43,277
Don't do this.

1571
01:03:43,861 --> 01:03:45,696
Come on, don't do this. Seriously.

1572
01:03:45,780 --> 01:03:48,157
Why are you guys… Don't help.

1573
01:03:49,784 --> 01:03:51,869
I told you, you don't have to help.

1574
01:03:52,453 --> 01:03:54,580
I told you no. Why don't you listen?

1575
01:03:54,664 --> 01:03:55,706
We should get the coffee.

1576
01:03:55,790 --> 01:03:57,875
- Woo-seok and I will pick up the coffee.
- Great.

1577
01:03:58,459 --> 01:03:59,460
- Let's go.
- Okay.

1578
01:04:00,336 --> 01:04:03,422
Getting out and driving
somewhere is sort of like a break.

1579
01:04:04,882 --> 01:04:06,717
That's why I wanted to come.

1580
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:09,637
Ow, my back.

1581
01:04:09,720 --> 01:04:10,930
- Wow.
- Oh, man.

1582
01:04:12,306 --> 01:04:15,017
By the way, the food turned out
really good, right?

1583
01:04:15,101 --> 01:04:16,602
Yeah, much better than expected, huh?

1584
01:04:16,686 --> 01:04:17,728
I was surprised.

1585
01:04:17,812 --> 01:04:20,857
But how did the kimchi fried rice
turn out so good?

1586
01:04:20,940 --> 01:04:22,942
I thought we totally messed it up.

1587
01:04:23,025 --> 01:04:24,735
Right? That's what I want to know.

1588
01:04:35,246 --> 01:04:36,539
Wait, Ye-eun.

1589
01:04:36,622 --> 01:04:38,207
- Yeah?
- Did you see this?

1590
01:04:38,291 --> 01:04:39,542
Five "so-sos."

1591
01:04:39,625 --> 01:04:41,168
THE WORST RATING SO FAR

1592
01:04:41,252 --> 01:04:44,755
It's just that every one of you
was saying it was really good.

1593
01:04:46,090 --> 01:04:48,342
WHO PUT THE YELLOW BALLS IN?

1594
01:04:50,344 --> 01:04:51,345
"So-so"?

1595
01:04:52,221 --> 01:04:54,098
You enjoyed it the most
and you gave it a "so-so?"

1596
01:04:54,974 --> 01:04:56,767
I CHOOSE "SO-SO" TOO

1597
01:04:56,851 --> 01:04:58,561
- Did you vote?
- Just about to.

1598
01:04:59,312 --> 01:05:00,730
- Really, "so-so"?
- Sorry.

1599
01:05:01,564 --> 01:05:02,940
- "So-so."
- We can write down what we want.

1600
01:05:03,524 --> 01:05:05,943
Oh. They didn't see me do that, right?
I'll cover you.

1601
01:05:06,027 --> 01:05:07,445
MIN-JU, WHO GOT SECONDS
OF THE KIMCHI FRIED RICE

1602
01:05:07,528 --> 01:05:09,030
- Okay, now it's my turn.
- You don't mean that.

1603
01:05:09,113 --> 01:05:12,283
- I'm a so-so.
- Right? It's only fair.

1604
01:05:13,075 --> 01:05:15,953
AND THAT'S
HOW THEY GOT FIVE OF THEM

1605
01:05:16,037 --> 01:05:18,623
We cleaned so fast with everyone helping.

1606
01:05:18,706 --> 01:05:21,417
Thanks to you, we finished so early.

1607
01:05:21,500 --> 01:05:23,044
- We got coffee.
- Coffee delivery.

1608
01:05:23,127 --> 01:05:24,795
Oh, Hyung.

1609
01:05:24,879 --> 01:05:25,880
Have some coffee.

1610
01:05:25,963 --> 01:05:28,674
CHATTERING AWAY
OVER COFFEE

1611
01:05:28,758 --> 01:05:30,092
So, where's your wife?

1612
01:05:30,635 --> 01:05:32,345
She's probably out somewhere.

1613
01:05:32,428 --> 01:05:34,055
This is a vacation for her.

1614
01:05:34,138 --> 01:05:35,681
- We all need that.
- Yeah.

1615
01:05:35,765 --> 01:05:37,934
Do you want to go on a vacation too?

1616
01:05:38,935 --> 01:05:40,603
- Me?
- By yourself?

1617
01:05:40,686 --> 01:05:41,687
I just…

1618
01:05:42,563 --> 01:05:43,773
want to be home.

1619
01:05:46,317 --> 01:05:47,360
INNER THOUGHTS BLURTED OUT

1620
01:05:47,443 --> 01:05:48,444
Are you…

1621
01:05:48,527 --> 01:05:50,988
- Oh, right. I can't ask your age.
- How old do you think I am?

1622
01:05:51,072 --> 01:05:52,323
You'll learn eventually.

1623
01:05:52,406 --> 01:05:54,033
- Can I be honest?
- Sure.

1624
01:05:54,116 --> 01:05:55,368
No, no, it's okay.

1625
01:05:55,451 --> 01:05:57,453
You're going to be scarred, though.

1626
01:05:57,536 --> 01:05:59,997
My guess will stick with you
your whole life. Can you handle that?

1627
01:06:00,081 --> 01:06:01,207
Yeah.

1628
01:06:01,290 --> 01:06:05,002
- I'd say you're in your mid-30s.
- Mid-30s.

1629
01:06:05,086 --> 01:06:06,462
Seriously?

1630
01:06:06,545 --> 01:06:07,672
All right.

1631
01:06:07,755 --> 01:06:09,215
Oh, are you in your 20s?

1632
01:06:09,882 --> 01:06:11,384
Don't tell us. Don't tell us yet.

1633
01:06:11,467 --> 01:06:14,053
Actually, I think that's
the highest number I've ever gotten.

1634
01:06:14,637 --> 01:06:15,680
What?

1635
01:06:15,763 --> 01:06:18,432
- Wait, I thought he was older than me.
- Come on.

1636
01:06:18,516 --> 01:06:21,227
You also look like you could
be in your 20s.

1637
01:06:21,310 --> 01:06:23,312
- Okay.
- I keep going back and forth.

1638
01:06:23,396 --> 01:06:25,481
Funny. He keeps going back and forth.

1639
01:06:26,524 --> 01:06:29,568
- Yeah, I can't decide.
- Oh. But I think I can see it.

1640
01:06:29,652 --> 01:06:31,362
- I've come to accept it. Yeah.
- Right.

1641
01:06:31,445 --> 01:06:33,114
We're getting pretty far out.

1642
01:06:34,532 --> 01:06:37,326
A SUSPICIOUS CAR'S
HEADING INTO JAE-SEOK'S B&B

1643
01:06:37,410 --> 01:06:39,829
So when we arrive,
you think Yu Jae-seok will be there?

1644
01:06:41,122 --> 01:06:42,123
Look at that.

1645
01:06:42,206 --> 01:06:44,166
- "Jae-seok's B&B."
- They put up a sign.

1646
01:06:45,001 --> 01:06:46,836
WHO ARE THESE PEOPLE
HEADING TO JAE-SEOK'S B&B?

1647
01:06:46,919 --> 01:06:51,173
It feels like we're going to boot camp.

1648
01:06:51,257 --> 01:06:55,011
Hello, I'm the director
of Hyo-ri's Homestay, Ms. Lee Hyo-ri.

1649
01:06:55,094 --> 01:06:56,095
Hello.

1650
01:06:57,054 --> 01:06:58,681
I'm the owner, Lee Sang-soon.

1651
01:06:58,764 --> 01:07:02,643
We started this whole
B&B variety show trend.

1652
01:07:02,727 --> 01:07:04,145
We're the originals, right?

1653
01:07:04,228 --> 01:07:06,605
Then we heard
Jae-seok was doing this show,

1654
01:07:06,689 --> 01:07:08,858
so we came here to give him our support.

1655
01:07:08,941 --> 01:07:11,861
We also wanted to experience it again.
It's been a while.

1656
01:07:11,944 --> 01:07:13,279
So that's what's brought us here.

1657
01:07:13,362 --> 01:07:14,613
SPECIAL HELPERS TO KEEP
THE ROOKIE IN CHECK

1658
01:07:15,781 --> 01:07:17,533
Okay, we're here.

1659
01:07:18,534 --> 01:07:20,536
Hold on.

1660
01:07:21,537 --> 01:07:23,998
HYO-RI GETS BACK IN THE CAR

1661
01:07:24,081 --> 01:07:27,835
Wait, I want to get out with a smile.

1662
01:07:28,669 --> 01:07:29,670
A RATHER CALCULATED EXIT

1663
01:07:29,754 --> 01:07:31,630
- Wow. The weather's nice.
- What is it?

1664
01:07:32,256 --> 01:07:34,216
Hold on, let's grab our stuff first.

1665
01:07:34,925 --> 01:07:36,302
You think I should bring my guitar?

1666
01:07:36,385 --> 01:07:37,845
Well, that'll look like…

1667
01:07:37,928 --> 01:07:39,930
It'll look like we came prepared.

1668
01:07:40,014 --> 01:07:41,098
PREPARING FOR CHECK-IN
WITH A PLAN

1669
01:07:41,182 --> 01:07:44,226
I think Jae-seok already knows.
Oh, Kwang-soo?

1670
01:07:44,852 --> 01:07:47,855
CALLING KWANG-SOO,
PRETENDING TO BE A LATE GUEST

1671
01:07:47,938 --> 01:07:50,232
One of them runs their own business,
so people are like--

1672
01:07:50,316 --> 01:07:51,734
- What?
- It's no wonder.

1673
01:07:51,817 --> 01:07:52,902
Wait, really?

1674
01:07:53,527 --> 01:07:55,321
- I mean, everyone thinks like that.
- I didn't mean…

1675
01:07:55,404 --> 01:07:57,073
- Everyone.
- That's not it.

1676
01:07:58,949 --> 01:07:59,992
Oh.

1677
01:08:00,576 --> 01:08:02,661
EXCITED

1678
01:08:02,745 --> 01:08:03,746
Hello?

1679
01:08:04,288 --> 01:08:05,748
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1680
01:08:05,831 --> 01:08:08,209
- Mr. Lee Kwang-soo?
- Yes.

1681
01:08:08,292 --> 01:08:11,253
Oh, I'm a guest
who got here a little late.

1682
01:08:12,671 --> 01:08:14,924
- Oh, okay.
- Can I come in now?

1683
01:08:17,426 --> 01:08:18,761
Hello?

1684
01:08:18,844 --> 01:08:21,222
- Hyung, there's a guest who arrived late.
- What?

1685
01:08:21,305 --> 01:08:23,140
Uh… You mean there's someone else coming?

1686
01:08:23,224 --> 01:08:25,810
I thought you were
sending a limo to pick us up.

1687
01:08:27,269 --> 01:08:29,522
- A limo?
- <i>Yes.</i>

1688
01:08:30,106 --> 01:08:31,565
- A limo?
- Who is this?

1689
01:08:31,649 --> 01:08:33,984
You've got the red carpet
rolled out for us, right?

1690
01:08:35,444 --> 01:08:37,238
Roll out the red carpet?

1691
01:08:37,321 --> 01:08:38,489
Who is this?

1692
01:08:38,572 --> 01:08:39,740
It's Hyo-ri.

1693
01:08:39,824 --> 01:08:41,033
Oh!

1694
01:08:41,117 --> 01:08:42,993
Hyo-ri's coming?

1695
01:08:43,077 --> 01:08:45,371
- No.
- What?

1696
01:08:45,454 --> 01:08:46,664
- For real?
- I think so.

1697
01:08:46,747 --> 01:08:47,957
Really?

1698
01:08:48,040 --> 01:08:49,667
THE ORIGINAL GUESTHOUSE HOSTS,
HYO-RI AND SANG-SOON,

1699
01:08:49,750 --> 01:08:50,751
HAVE COME TO JAE-SEOK'S B&B

1700
01:08:50,835 --> 01:08:53,712
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!
